column9: From (H4998) na'ah or (H5116) naveh; suitable, or beautiful -- becometh, comely, seemly. see HEBREW (H4998) na'ah see HEBREW (H5116) naveh

column7: to utter a prophecy, speak as a prophet
column9: A primitive root; properly, to whisper, i.e. (by implication) to utter as a oracle -- say.
From (H5001) na'am; an oracle -- (hath) said, saith. see HEBREW (H5001) na'am

column8: adultereress, committing adultery, woman that breaks wedlock
column9: A primitive root; to commit adultery; figuratively, to apostatize -- adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.
From (H5003) na'aph; adultery -- adultery. see HEBREW (H5003) na'aph
From (H5003) na'aph; adultery -- adultery. see HEBREW (H5003) na'aph

column8: abhor, give occasion to blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, great, provoke
column9: A primitive root; to scorn; or (Ecclesiastes 12:5) by interchange for (H5132) nuwts, to bloom -- abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, X great, provoke. see HEBREW (H5132) nuwts
Or nematsah {neh-aw-tsaw'}; from (H5006) na'ats; scorn -- blasphemy. see HEBREW (H5006) na'ats
A primitive root; to groan -- groan.
From (H5008) na'aq; a groan -- groaning. see HEBREW (H5008) na'aq
A primitive root; to reject -- abhor, make void.

column7: a priestly city, perhaps also a place North of Jer
column9: The same as (H5108) nowb; fruit; Nob, a place in Palestine -- Nob. see HEBREW (H5108) nowb
A primitive root; to prophesy, i.e. Speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse) -- prophesy(-ing), make self a prophet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5012) naba' -- prophesy. see HEBREW (H5012) naba'
A primitive root; to pierce; to be hollow, or (figuratively) foolish -- hollow, vain.

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, of a divinity
column7: a city in Moab, also a mountain in Moab
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Nebo, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine -- Nebo.
From (H5012) naba'; a prediction (spoken or written) -- prophecy. see HEBREW (H5012) naba'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5016) nbuw'ah; inspired teaching -- prophesying. see HEBREW (H5016) nbuw'ah

column7: Nebo has given seed, a Bab. general
column9: Of foreign origin; Nebuzaradan, a Babylonian general -- Nebuzaradan.

column7: Nebo, protect the boundary, a Bab. king
column9: Or Nbukadneotstsar (2 Kings 24:1, 2 Kings 24:10) {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadnetstsar (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18) {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadreotstsar {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsar'}; or Nbuwkadreltstsowr (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28) {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsore'}; or foreign derivation; Nebukadnetstsar (or -retstsar, or -retstsor), king of Babylon -- Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar. see HEBREW (H10) 'abaddoh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5019) Nbuwkadne'tstsar -- Nebuchadnezzar. see HEBREW (H5019) Nbuwkadne'tstsar

column7: O Nebo, deliver me, a Bab. officer
column9: Of foreign derivation; Nebushazban, Nebuchadnezzar's chief eunuch -- Nebushazban.
Feminine plural from the same as (H5011) Nob; fruits; Naboth, an Israelite -- Naboth. see HEBREW (H5011) Nob
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a largess -- reward.
A primitive root; to bark (as a dog) -- bark.

column4: proper name, masculine and of a location; masculine; location
column7: a place in Gilead, also a Manassite
column9: From (H5024) nabach; a bark; Nobach, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan -- Nobah. see HEBREW (H5024) nabach
Of foreign origin; Nibchaz, a deity of the Avites -- Nibhaz.

column8: cause to behold, consider, look down, regard, have respect, see
column9: A primitive root; to scan, i.e. Look intently at; by implication, to regard with pleasure, favor or care -- (cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.
From (H5027) nabat; regard; Nebat, the father of Jeroboam I -- Nebat. see HEBREW (H5027) nabat
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5030) nabiy'; a prophet -- prophet. see HEBREW (H5030) nabiy'
From (H5012) naba'; a prophet or (generally) inspired man -- prophecy, that prophesy, prophet. see HEBREW (H5012) naba'
Feminine of (H5030) nabiy'; a prophetess or (generally) inspired woman; by implication, a poetess; by association a prophet's wife -- prophetess. see HEBREW (H5030) nabiy'

column7: oldest son of Ishmael, also his desc
column9: Or Nbayoth {neb-aw-yoth'}; feminine plural from (H5107) nuwb; fruitfulnesses; Nebajoth, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him -- Nebaioth, Nebajoth. see HEBREW (H5107) nuwb
From an unused root meaning to burst forth; a fountain -- spring.

column8: disgrace, dishounor, lightly esteem, come to nothing, make vile, wither
column9: A primitive root; to wilt; generally, to fall away, fail, faint; figuratively, to be foolish or (morally) wicked; causatively, to despise, disgrace -- disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, - ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, X surely, make vile, wither.

column7: a skin bottle, skin, jar, pitcher
column9: Or nebel {nay'-bel}; from (H5034) nabel; a skin-bag for liquids (from collapsing when empty); hence, a vase (as similar in shape when full); also a lyre (as having a body of like form) -- bottle, pitcher, psaltery, vessel, viol. see HEBREW (H5034) nabel
From (H5034) nabel; stupid; wicked (especially impious) -- fool(-ish, -ish man, -ish woman), vile person. see HEBREW (H5034) nabel
The same as (H5036) nabal; dolt; Nabal, an Israelite -- Nabal. see HEBREW (H5036) nabal

column8: dead body, dead carcass, dead of itself, which died, beast that which dieth of itself
column9: From (H5034) nabel; a flabby thing, i.e. A carcase or carrion (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an idol -- (dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself. see HEBREW (H5034) nabel
Feminine of (H5036) nabal; foolishness, i.e. (morally) wickedness; concretely, a crime; by extension, punishment -- folly, vile, villany. see HEBREW (H5036) nabal
From (H5036) nabal; properly, disgrace, i.e. The (female) pudenda -- lewdness. see HEBREW (H5036) nabal
Apparently from (H5036) nabal and (H3909) lat; foolish secrecy; Neballat, a place in Palestine -- Neballat. see HEBREW (H5036) nabal see HEBREW (H3909) lat

column8: Pour out, flowing, send forth, utter abundantly
column9: A primitive root; to gush forth; figuratively, to utter (good or bad words); specifically, to emit (a foul odor) -- belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).
(Aramaic) from an unused root meaning to shine; a light; plural (collectively) a chandelier -- candlestick.
Of uncertain derivation; Nibshan, a place in Palestine -- Nibshan.

From an unused root meaning to be parched; the south (from its drought); specifically, the Negeb or southern district of Judah, occasionally, Egypt (as south to Palestine) -- south (country, side, -ward).

column8: bewray, certainly, certify, declare, denounce, expound, fully, messenger,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to front, i.e. Stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to manifest; figuratively, to announce (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to expose, predict, explain, praise -- bewray, X certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, X fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, X surely, tell, utter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5046) nagad; to flow (through the idea of clearing the way) -- issue. see HEBREW (H5046) nagad

column7: in front of, in sight of, opposite to
column8: about, over against, aloof, far off, from, over, presence, other side,
column9: From (H5046) nagad; a front, i.e. Part opposite; specifically a counterpart, or mate; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) over against or before -- about, (over) against, X aloof, X far (off), X from, over, presence, X other side, sight, X to view. see HEBREW (H5046) nagad
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5048) neged; opposite -- toward. see HEBREW (H5048) neged
A primitive root; to glitter; causatively, to illuminate -- (en-)lighten, (cause to) shine.
From (H5050) nagahh; brilliancy (literally or figuratively) -- bright(-ness), light, (clear) shining. see HEBREW (H5050) nagahh
The same as (H5051) nogahh; Nogah, a son of David -- Nogah. see HEBREW (H5051) nogahh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5051) nogahh; dawn -- morning. see HEBREW (H5051) nogahh
Feminine of (H5051) nogahh; splendor -- brightness. see HEBREW (H5051) nogahh
A primitive root; to but with the horns; figuratively, to war against -- gore, push (down, -ing).
From (H5055) nagach; butting, i.e. Vicious -- used (wont) to push. see HEBREW (H5055) nagach

column8: captain, chief, excellent thing, chief governor, leader, noble, prince, chief ruler
column9: Or nagid {naw-gheed'}; from (H5046) nagad; a commander (as occupying the front), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), honorable themes -- captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler. see HEBREW (H5046) nagad

column8: stringed instrument, music, Neginoth plural, song
column9: Or ngiynath (Psa. (H61) 'abal:title) {neg-ee-nath'}; from (H5059) nagan; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a stringed instrument; by extension, a poem set to music; specifically, an epigram -- stringed instrument, musick, Neginoth (plural), song. see HEBREW (H5059) nagan

column7: to touch or play a stringed instrument
column8: player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, player,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to thrum, i.e. Beat a tune with the fingers; expec. To play on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to make music -- player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).

column8: beat, be able to bring down, cast, come nigh, draw near nigh, get up, happen, join,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to touch, i.e. Lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphem., to lie with a woman); by implication, to reach (figuratively, to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.) -- beat, (X be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.

column8: plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound
column9: From (H5060) naga'; a blow (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a spot (concretely, a leprous person or dress) -- plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound. see HEBREW (H5060) naga'

column8: beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite down, strike, stumble,
column9: A primitive root; to push, gore, defeat, stub (the toe), inflict (a disease) -- beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, X surely, put to the worse.
From (H5062) nagaph; a trip (of the foot); figuratively, an infliction (of disease) -- plague, stumbling. see HEBREW (H5062) nagaph

column8: fall, flow away, pour down out, run, shed, spilt, trickle down
column9: A primitive root; to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over -- fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.

column8: distress, driver, exactor, oppressor, raiser of taxes, taskmaster
column9: A primitive root; to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize -- distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), X raiser of taxes, taskmaster.

column8: make to approach nigh, bring forth, hither, near, cause to come hither, near, nigh, give place,
column9: A primitive root; to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; relig. To worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back -- (make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.
From (H5110) nuwd in the sense of piling up; a mound, i.e. Wave -- heap. see HEBREW (H5110) nuwd

column8: offer freely, be give, make, offer self willingly
column9: A primitive root; to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously -- offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5068) nadab; be (or give) liberal(-ly) -- (be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly). see HEBREW (H5068) nadab
From (H5068) nadab; liberal; Nadab, the name of four Israelites -- Nadab. see HEBREW (H5068) nadab

column8: freewill offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary, offering, willingly, offering
column9: From (H5068) nadab; properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift -- free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering). see HEBREW (H5068) nadab

column7: whom Yah impels, a son of Jeconiah
column9: From (H5068) nadab and (H3050) Yahh; largess of Jah; Nedabjah, an Israelite -- Nedabiah. see HEBREW (H5068) nadab see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
(Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick; a layer (of building materials) -- row.

column7: to retreat, flee, depart, stray, wander, flutter
column8: chase away, could not, depart, flee apace, away, remove, thrust away, wander abroad,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away -- chase (away), X could not, depart, flee (X apace, away), (re-)move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5074) nadad; to depart -- go from. see HEBREW (H5074) nadad
Passive participle of (H5074) nadad; properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed) -- tossing to and fro. see HEBREW (H5074) nadad

column8: cast out, drive, put far away
column9: Or nada (2 Kings 17:21) {naw-daw'}; a primitive root; properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. Banish, postpone, prohibit -- cast out, drive, put far away.
From (H5077) nadah in the sense of freely flinging money; a bounty (for prostitution) -- gifts. see HEBREW (H5077) nadah

column8: far, filthiness, flowers, menstruous woman, put apart, removed woman
column9: From (H5074) nadad; properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest) -- X far, filthiness, X flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, X removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness). see HEBREW (H5074) nadad

column8: banish, bring, cast down out, chase, compel, draw away, drive away, out,
column9: A primitive root; to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.) -- banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.

column8: free, liberal things, noble, prince, willing hearted
column9: From (H5068) nadab; properly, voluntary, i.e. Generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant) -- free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing ((hearted)). see HEBREW (H5068) nadab
Feminine of (H5081) nadiyb; properly, nobility, i.e. Reputation -- soul. see HEBREW (H5081) nadiyb
Probably from an unused root meaning to give; a present (for prostitution) -- gift.
Of uncertain derivation; a sheath (of a sword) -- sheath.
(Aramaic) from the same as (H5084) nadan; a sheath; figuratively, the body (as the receptacle of the soul) -- body. see HEBREW (H5084) nadan

column8: drive away, to and fro, thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro
column9: A primitive root; to shove asunder, i.e. Disperse -- drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.
A primitive root; to promise (pos., to do or give something to God) -- (make a) vow.
Or neder {nay'-der}; from (H5087) nadar; a promise (to God); also (concretely) a thing promised -- vow((-ed)). see HEBREW (H5087) nadar
From an unused root meaning to lament; lamentation -- wailing.

column8: acquaint, bring away, carry away, drive away, lead away, forth, be guide, lead away,
column9: A primitive root; to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. Lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. Impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh -- acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).
A primitive root; to groan, i.e. Bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation) -- lament, wail.
From (H5091) nahah; an elegy -- lamentation, wailing. see HEBREW (H5091) nahah
Feminine of (H5092) nhiy; lamentation -- doleful. see HEBREW (H5092) nhiy
(Aramaic) or nehiyruw (Aramaic) {neh-hee-roo'}; from the same as (H5105) nharah; illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom -- light. see HEBREW (H5105) nharah

column7: to lead or guide to a watering place, bring to a place of rest, refresh
column8: carry, feed, guide, lead gently, on
column9: A primitive root; properly, to run with a sparkle, i.e. Flow; hence (transitively), to conduct, and (by inference) to protect, sustain -- carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on).
Or Nahalol {nah-hal-ole'}; the same as (H5097) nahalol; Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine -- Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol. see HEBREW (H5097) nahalol
From (H5095) nahal; pasture -- bush. see HEBREW (H5095) nahal
A primitive root; to growl -- mourn, roar(-ing).
From (H5098) naham; a snarl -- roaring. see HEBREW (H5098) naham
Feminine of (H5099) naham; snarling -- disquietness, roaring. see HEBREW (H5099) naham
A primitive root; to bray (as an ass), scream (from hunger -- bray.
A primitive root; to sparkle, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; hence (from the sheen of a running stream) to flow, i.e. (figuratively) assemble -- flow (together), be lightened.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5102) nahar; a river, especially the Euphrates -- river, stream. see HEBREW (H5102) nahar
From (H5102) nahar; a stream (including the sea; expec. The Nile, Euphrates, etc.); figuratively, prosperity -- flood, river. see HEBREW (H5102) nahar
From (H5102) nahar in its original sense; daylight -- light. see HEBREW (H5102) nahar

column8: break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect
column9: A primitive root; to refuse, forbid, dissuade, or neutralize -- break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.

column8: bring forth fruit, make cheerful, increase
column9: A primitive root; to germinate, i.e. (figuratively) to (causatively, make) flourish; also (of words), to utter -- bring forth (fruit), make cheerful, increase.
Or neyb {nabe}; from (H5107) nuwb; produce, literally or figuratively -- fruit. see HEBREW (H5107) nuwb
From (H5108) nowb; fruitful; Nobai, an Israelite -- Nebai (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5108) nowb

column7: to move to and fro, wander, flutter, show grief
column8: bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake,
column9: A primitive root; to nod, i.e. Waver; figuratively, to wander, flee, disappear; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to console, deplore, or (from tossing the head in scorn) taunt -- bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5116) naveh; to flee -- get away. see HEBREW (H5116) naveh
(only defect. Nod {node}); from (H5110) nuwd; exile -- wandering. see HEBREW (H5110) nuwd

column7: a region into which Cain wandered
column9: The same as (H5112) nowd; vagrancy; Nod, the land of Cain -- Nod. see HEBREW (H5112) nowd
From (H5068) nadab; noble; Nodab, an Arab tribe -- Nodab. see HEBREW (H5068) nadab

column8: keept at home, prepare an habitation
column9: A primitive root; to rest (as at home); causatively (through the implied idea of beauty (compare (H5116) naveh)), to celebrate (with praises) -- keept at home, prepare an habitation. see HEBREW (H5116) naveh

column7: abode of shepherd or flocks, habitation
column8: comely, dwelling place, fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried
column9: Or (feminine) navah {naw-vaw'}; from (H5115) navah; (adjectively) at home; hence (by implication of satisfaction) lovely; also (noun) a home, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (den) -- comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried. see HEBREW (H5115) navah

column8: cease, be confederate, lay, let down, be quiet, remain, cause to, be at,
column9: A primitive root; to rest, i.e. Settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.) -- cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare (H3241) Yaniym. see HEBREW (H3241) Yaniym
Or nowach {no'-akh}; from (H5117) nuwach; quiet -- rest(-ed, -ing place). see HEBREW (H5117) nuwach
Feminine of (H5118) nuwach; quietude; Nochah, an Israelite -- Nohah. see HEBREW (H5118) nuwach
To quake -- be moved.
From (H5115) navah; residence; Navith, a place in Palestine -- Naioth (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5115) navah
(Aramaic) or nvaliy (Aramaic) {nev-aw-lee'}; from an unused root probably meaning to be foul; a sink -- dunghill.
A primitive root; to slumber (from drowsiness) -- sleep, slumber.
From (H5123) nuwm; sleepiness -- drowsiness. see HEBREW (H5123) nuwm
A primitive root; to resprout, i.e. Propagate by shoots; figuratively, to be perpetual -- be continued.
Or Nown (1 Chron. 7:27) {nohn}; from (H5125) nuwn; perpetuity, Nun or Non, the father of Joshua -- Non, Nun. see HEBREW (H5125) nuwn

column8: abate, away, be displayed, make to flee away put to flight, hide, lift up a standard
column9: A primitive root; to flit, i.e. Vanish away (subside, escape; causatively, chase, impel, deliver) -- X abate, away, be displayed, (make to) flee (away, -ing), put to flight, X hide, lift up a standard.

column7: to quiver, wave, waver, tremble, totter
column8: continually, fugitive, make, to go up and down, be gone away
column9: A primitive root; to waver, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined) -- continually, fugitive, X make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).

column7: meeting with Yah, a Levite, also a prophetess
column9: From (H3259) ya'ad and (H3050) Yahh; convened of Jah; Noadjah, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess -- Noadiah. see HEBREW (H3259) ya'ad see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to move to and fro, wave, sprinkle
column8: lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike,
column9: A primitive root; to quiver (i.e. Vibrate up and down, or rock to and fro); used in a great variety of applications (including sprinkling, beckoning, rubbing, bastinadoing, sawing, waving, etc.) -- lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike, wave.
From (H5130) nuwph; elevation -- situation. Compare (H5297) Noph. see HEBREW (H5130) nuwph see HEBREW (H5297) Noph
A primitive root; properly, to flash; hence, to blossom (from the brilliancy of color); also, to fly away (from the quickness of motion) -- flee away, bud (forth).
Or notsah {no-tsaw'}; feminine active participle of (H5327) natsah in the sense of flying; a pinion (or wing feather); often (collectively) plumage -- feather(-s), ostrich. see HEBREW (H5327) natsah
A primitive root; to suckle -- nurse.
(Aramaic) from an unused root (corresponding to that of (H5216) niyr) meaning to shine; fire -- fiery, fire. see HEBREW (H5216) niyr
A primitive root; to be sick, i.e. (figuratively) distressed -- be full of heaviness.
A primitive root; to spirt, i.e. Besprinkle (especially in expiation) -- sprinkle.
From (H2102) zuwd; something boiled, i.e. Soup -- pottage. see HEBREW (H2102) zuwd

Or nazir {naw-zeer'}; from (H5144) nazar; separate, i.e. Consecrated (as prince, a Nazirite); hence (figuratively from the latter) an unpruned vine (like an unshorn Nazirite) -- Nazarite (by a false alliteration with Nazareth), separate(-d), vine undressed. see HEBREW (H5144) nazar

column8: distil, drop, flood, cause to flowing, gush out, melt, pour down, running water,
column9: A primitive root; to drip, or shed by trickling -- distil, drop, flood, (cause to) flow(-ing), gush out, melt, pour (down), running water, stream.
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a nose-ring -- earring, jewel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of (H5143) nezeq; to suffer (causatively, inflict) loss -- have (en-)damage, hurt(-ful). see HEBREW (H5143) nezeq
From an unused root meaning to injure; loss -- damage.

A primitive root; to hold aloof, i.e. (intransitivey) abstain (from food and drink, from impurity, and even from divine worship (i.e. Apostatize)); specifically, to set apart (to sacred purposes), i.e. Devote -- consecrate, separate(-ing, self).

Or nezer {nay'-zer}; from (H5144) nazar; properly, something set apart, i.e. (abstractly) dedication (of a priet or Nazirite); hence (concretely) unshorn locks; also (by implication) a chaplet (especially of royalty) -- consecration, crown, hair, separation. see HEBREW (H5144) nazar

column7: rest, patriarch who survived the flood
column9: The same as (H5118) nuwach; rest; Noach, the patriarch of the flood -- Noah. see HEBREW (H5118) nuwach
From (H2247) chabah; occult; Nachbi, an Israelite -- Nakbi. see HEBREW (H2247) chabah

column8: bestow, bring, govern, guide, lead forth, put, straiten
column9: A primitive root; to guide; by implication, to transport (into exile, or as colonists) -- bestow, bring, govern, guide, lead (forth), put, straiten.

column7: comfort, an Israelite of Nehemiah\'s time
column9: From (H5162) nacham; comforted; Nechum, an Israelite -- Nehum. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
Or nichum {nee-khoom'}; from (H5162) nacham; properly, consoled; abstractly, solace -- comfort(-able), repenting. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
From (H5162) nacham; comfortable; Nachum, an Israelite prophet -- Nahum. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham

column7: grandfather of Abraham, also the brother of Abraham
column9: From the same as (H5170) nachar; snorer; Nochor, the name of the grandfather and a brother of Abraham -- Nahor. see HEBREW (H5170) nachar

Apparently passive participle of (H5172) nachash (perhaps in the sense of ringing, i.e. Bell-metal; or from the red color of the throat of a serpent ((H5175) nachash, as denominative) when hissing); coppery, i.e. (figuratively) hard -- of brass. see HEBREW (H5172) nachash see HEBREW (H5175) nachash
Or nchushah {nekh-oo-shaw'}; feminine of (H5153) nachuwsh; copper -- brass, steel. Compare (H5176) Nachash. see HEBREW (H5153) nachuwsh see HEBREW (H5176) Nachash
Probably denominative from (H2485) chaliyl; a flute -- (plural) Nehiloth. see HEBREW (H2485) chaliyl
From the same as (H5170) nachar; a nostril -- (dual) nostrils. see HEBREW (H5170) nachar

column7: to get or take as a possession
column8: divide, have inheritance, take as a heritage, cause to, give to, make to inherit, distribute for
column9: A primitive root; to inherit (as a (figurative) mode of descent), or (generally) to occupy; causatively, to bequeath, or (generally) distribute, instate -- divide, have ((inheritance)), take as a heritage, (cause to, give to, make to) inherit, (distribute for, divide (for, for an, by), give for, have, leave for, take (for)) inheritance, (have in, cause to, be made to) possess(-ion).

Or (feminine) nachlah (Psalm 124:4) {nakh'-law}; or nachalah (Ezekiel 47:19; 48:28) {nakh-al-aw'}; from (H5157) nachal in its original sense; a stream, especially a winter torrent; (by implication) a (narrow) valley (in which a brook runs); also a shaft (of a mine) -- brook, flood, river, stream, valley. see HEBREW (H5157) nachal

From (H5157) nachal (in its usual sense); properly, something inherited, i.e. (abstractly) occupancy, or (concretely) an heirloom; generally an estate, patrimony or portion -- heritage, to inherit, inheritance, possession. Compare (H5158) nachal. see HEBREW (H5157) nachal see HEBREW (H5158) nachal

column7: valley of God, a place East of the Dead Sea
column9: From (H5158) nachal and (H410) 'el; valley of God; Nachaliel, a place in the Desert -- Nahaliel. see HEBREW (H5158) nachal see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: descriptive title for a false prophet
column9: Apparently a patronymic from an unused name (apparently passive participle of (H2492) chalam); dreamed; a Nechelamite, or descendant of Nechlam -- Nehelamite. see HEBREW (H2492) chalam

column8: comfort self, ease one\'s self, repent,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to sigh, i.e. Breathe strongly; by implication, to be sorry, i.e. (in a favorable sense) to pity, console or (reflexively) rue; or (unfavorably) to avenge (oneself) -- comfort (self), ease (one's self), repent(-er,-ing, self).
From (H5162) nacham; consolation; Nacham, an Israelite -- Naham. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
From (H5162) nacham; ruefulness, i.e. Desistance -- repentance. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
From (H5162) nacham; consolation -- comfort. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
From (H5162) nacham and (H3050) Yahh; consolation of Jah; Nechemjah, the name of three Israelites -- Nehemiah. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: compassionate, an Israelite of Nehemiah\'s time
column9: From (H5162) nacham; consolatory; Nachamani, an Israelite -- Nahamani. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
For (H587) 'anachnuw; we -- we. see HEBREW (H587) 'anachnuw
A primitive root; to be urgent -- require haste.
And (feminine) nacharah {nakh-ar-aw'}; from an unused root meaning to snort or snore; a snorting -- nostrils, snorting.
Or Nachray {nakh-rah'-ee}; from the same as (H5170) nachar; snorer; Nacharai or Nachrai, an Israelite -- Naharai, Nahari. see HEBREW (H5170) nachar

column8: certainly, divine, enchanter, use enchantment, learn by experience, diligently observe
column9: A primitive root; properly, to hiss, i.e. Whisper a (magic) spell; generally, to prognosticate -- X certainly, divine, enchanter, (use) X enchantment, learn by experience, X indeed, diligently observe.
From (H5172) nachash; an incantation or augury -- enchantment. see HEBREW (H5172) nachash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5154) nchuwshah; copper -- brass. see HEBREW (H5154) nchuwshah
From (H5172) nachash; a snake (from its hiss) -- serpent. see HEBREW (H5172) nachash
The same as (H5175) nachash; Nachash, the name of two persons apparently non-Israelite -- Nahash. see HEBREW (H5175) nachash
From (H5172) nachash; enchanter; Nachshon, an Israelite -- Naashon, Nahshon. see HEBREW (H5172) nachash

column8: brasen, brass, chain, copper, fetter of brass, filthiness, steel
column9: For (H5154) nchuwshah; copper, hence, something made of that metal, i.e. Coin, a fetter; figuratively, base (as compared with gold or silver) -- brasen, brass, chain, copper, fetter (of brass), filthiness, steel. see HEBREW (H5154) nchuwshah
From (H5178) nchosheth; copper; Nechushta, an Israelitess -- Nehushta. see HEBREW (H5178) nchosheth

column7: the name of Moses\' bronze serpent
column9: From (H5178) nchosheth; something made of copper, i.e. The copper serpent of the Desert -- Nehushtan. see HEBREW (H5178) nchosheth

column8: be broken, cause to come down, enter, go down, press sore, settle, stick fast
column9: A primitive root; to sink, i.e. Descend; causatively, to press or lead down -- be broken, (cause to) come down, enter, go down, press sore, settle, stick fast.

column8: carry, come down, depose, lay up, place
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H5181) nachath; to descend; causatively, to bring away, deposit, depose -- carry, come down, depose, lay up, place. see HEBREW (H5181) nachath

column8: lighting down, quietness, to rest, be set on
column9: From (H5182) nchath; a descent, i.e. Imposition, unfavorable (punishment) or favorable (food); also (intransitively; perhaps from (H5117) nuwach), restfulness -- lighting down, quiet(-ness), to rest, be set on. see HEBREW (H5182) nchath see HEBREW (H5117) nuwach
The same as (H5183) Nachath; quiet; Nachath, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites -- Nahath. see HEBREW (H5183) Nachath
From (H5181) nachath; descending -- come down. see HEBREW (H5181) nachath

column7: to stretch out, spread out, extend, incline, bend
column8: afternoon, apply, bow down carry aside, decline, deliver, extend, go down
column9: A primitive root; to stretch or spread out; by implication, to bend away (including moral deflection); used in a great variety of application (as follows) -- + afternoon, apply, bow (down, - ing), carry aside, decline, deliver, extend, go down, be gone, incline, intend, lay, let down, offer, outstretched, overthrown, pervert, pitch, prolong, put away, shew, spread (out), stretch (forth, out), take (aside), turn (aside, away), wrest, cause to yield.
From (H5190) natal; laden -- that bear. see HEBREW (H5190) natal
From (H5197) nataph; a pendant for the ears (especially of pearls) -- chain, collar. see HEBREW (H5197) nataph
From (H5203) natash; a tendril (as an offshoot) -- battlement, branch, plant. see HEBREW (H5203) natash
A prim root; to lift; by implication, to impose -- bear, offer, take up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5190) natal; to raise -- take up. see HEBREW (H5190) natal
: from (H5190) natal; a burden -- weighty. see HEBREW (H5190) natal
A primitive root; properly, to strike in, i.e. Fix; specifically, to plant (literally or figuratively) -- fastened, plant(- er).
From (H5193) nata'; a plant; collectively, a plantation; abstractly, a planting -- plant. see HEBREW (H5193) nata'
From (H5193) nata'; a plant -- plant. see HEBREW (H5193) nata'
Plural of (H5194) neta'; Netaim, a place in Palestine -- plants. see HEBREW (H5194) neta'
A primitive root; to ooze, i.e. Distil gradually; by implication, to fall in drops; figuratively, to speak by inspiration -- drop(-ping), prophesy(-et).
From (H5197) nataph; a drop; specifically, an aromatic gum (probably stacte) -- drop, stacte. see HEBREW (H5197) nataph
From (H5197) nataph; distillation; Netophah, a place in Palestine -- Netophah. see HEBREW (H5197) nataph
Patronymic from (H5199) Ntophah; a Netophathite, or inhabitant of Netophah -- Netophathite. see HEBREW (H5199) Ntophah
A primitive root; to guard; figuratively, to cherish (anger) -- bear grudge, keep(-er), reserve.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5201) natar; to retain -- keep. see HEBREW (H5201) natar

column8: cast off, drawn, let fall, forsake, join battle, leave off, lie still, loose,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pound, i.e. Smite; by implication (as if beating out, and thus expanding) to disperse; also, to thrust off, down, out or upon (inclusively, reject, let alone, permit, remit, etc.) -- cast off, drawn, let fall, forsake, join (battle), leave (off), lie still, loose, spread (self) abroad, stretch out, suffer.
A doubtful word; apparently from (H5091) nahah; lamentation -- wailing. see HEBREW (H5091) nahah
From (H5110) nuwd; motion (of the lips in speech) -- moving. see HEBREW (H5110) nuwd
Feminine of (H5205) niyd; removal, i.e. Exile -- removed. see HEBREW (H5205) niyd
Or niychoach {nee-kho'-akh}; from (H5117) nuwach; properly, restful, i.e. Pleasant; abstractly, delight -- sweet (odour). see HEBREW (H5117) nuwach
(Aramaic) or (shorter) niychoach (Aramaic) {nee-kho'-akh}; corresponding to (H5207) nichowach; pleasure -- sweet odour (savour). see HEBREW (H5207) nichowach
From (H5125) nuwn; progeny -- son. see HEBREW (H5125) nuwn
Of foreign origin; Nineveh, the capital of Assyria -- Nineveh.
From (H5127) nuwc; fugitive -- that fleeth. see HEBREW (H5127) nuwc

column7: first month of the Jewish religious year
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Nisan, the first month of the Jewish sacred year -- Nisan.
From (H5340) natsats; a spark -- spark. see HEBREW (H5340) natsats
A root probably identical with that of (H5216) niyr, through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow; to till the soil -- break up. see HEBREW (H5216) niyr
Or nir {neer}; from (H5214) niyr; properly, plowing, i.e. (concretely) freshly plowed land -- fallow ground, plowing, tillage. see HEBREW (H5214) niyr

Or nir {neer}; also neyr {nare}; or ner {nare}; or (feminine) nerah {nay-raw'}; from a primitive root (see (H5214) niyr; (H5135) nuwr) properly, meaning to glisten; a lamp (i.e. The burner) or light (literally or figuratively) -- candle, lamp, light. see HEBREW (H5214) niyr see HEBREW (H5135) nuwr
A primitive root; to smite, i.e. Drive away -- be viler.
Or nakat {naw-kaw'}; from (H5217) naka'; smitten, i.e. (figuratively) afflicted -- broken, stricken, wounded. see HEBREW (H5217) naka'
From (H5218) nake'; properly, a smiting, i.e. (concretely) an aromatic gum (perhaps styrax) (as powdered) -- spicery(-ces). see HEBREW (H5218) nake'
From an unused root meaning to propagate; offspring -- nephew, son's son.

column8: beat, cast forth, clap, give wounds, go forward, indeed, kill, make slaughter,
column9: A primitive root; to strike (lightly or severely, literally or figuratively) -- beat, cast forth, clap, give (wounds), X go forward, X indeed, kill, make (slaughter), murderer, punish, slaughter, slay(-er, -ing), smite(-r, -ing), strike, be stricken, (give) stripes, X surely, wound.
From (H5221) nakah; a smiter, i.e. (figuratively) traducer -- abject. see HEBREW (H5221) nakah
Smitten, i.e. (literally) maimed, or (figuratively) dejected -- contrite, lame.
Probably of Egyptian origin; Neko, an Egyptian king -- Necho. Compare (H6549) Par'oh Nkoh. see HEBREW (H6549) Par'oh Nkoh
From (H3559) kuwn; prepared; Nakon, probably an Israelite -- Nachon. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn
From an unused root meaning to be straightforward; properly, the fore part; used adverbially, opposite -- before, over against.

column8: over against, before, directly, for, right on
column9: From the same as (H5226) nekach; properly, the front part; used adverbially (especially with preposition), opposite, in front of, forward, in behalf of -- (over) against, before, direct(-ly), for, right (on). see HEBREW (H5226) nekach
From the same as (H5226) nekach; straightforward, i.e. (figuratively), equitable, correct, or (abstractly), integrity -- plain, right, uprightness. see HEBREW (H5226) nekach
Feminine of (H5228) nakoach; properly, straightforwardness, i.e. (figuratively) integrity, or (concretely) a truth -- equity, right (thing), uprightness. see HEBREW (H5228) nakoach

column7: to be crafty, deceitful or knavish
column9: A prim root; to defraud, i.e. Act treacherously -- beguile, conspire, deceiver, deal subtilly.
From (H5230) nakal; deceit -- wile. see HEBREW (H5230) nakal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5233) nekec -- goods. see HEBREW (H5233) nekec
From an unused root meaning to accumulate; treasure -- riches, wealth.

column8: acknowledge, could, deliver, discern, dissemble, estrange, feign self to be another
column9: A primitive root; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. Look intently at; hence (with recognition implied), to acknowledge, be acquainted with, care for, respect, revere, or (with suspicion implied), to disregard, ignore, be strange toward, reject, resign, dissimulate (as if ignorant or disowning) -- acknowledge, X could, deliver, discern, dissemble, estrange, feign self to be another, know, take knowledge (notice), perceive, regard, (have) respect, behave (make) self strange(-ly).

column7: to act or treat as foreign or strange, to disguise
column9: Or noker {no'-ker}; from (H5234) nakar; something strange, i.e. Unexpected calamity -- strange. see HEBREW (H5234) nakar
From (H5234) nakar; foreign, or (concretely) a foreigner, or (abstractly) heathendom -- alien, strange (+ -er). see HEBREW (H5234) nakar

From (H5235) neker (second form); strange, in a variety of degrees and applications (foreign, non-relative, adulterous, different, wonderful) -- alien, foreigner, outlandish, strange(-r, woman). see HEBREW (H5235) neker
Probably for (H5219) nko'th; spicery, i.e. (generally) valuables -- precious things. see HEBREW (H5219) nko'th
Apparently a primitive root; to complete -- make an end.
From (H959) bazah, despised -- vile. see HEBREW (H959) bazah
Apparently for (H3223) Ymuw'el; Nemuel, the name of two Israelites -- Nemuel. see HEBREW (H3223) Ymuw'el
From (H5241) Nmuw'el; a Nemuelite, or descendant of Nemuel -- Nemuelite. see HEBREW (H5241) Nmuw'el

column7: branch to be cut down off, circumcise
column8: branch to be cut down off, circumcise
column9: A primitive root; to become clipped or (specifically) circumcised -- (branch to) be cut down (off), circumcise.
Feminine from (H5243) namal; an ant (probably from its almost bisected form) -- ant. see HEBREW (H5243) namal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5246) namer -- leopard. see HEBREW (H5246) namer

From an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. Be limpid (comp (H5247) Nimrah and (H5249) Nimriym); and thus to spot or stain as if by dripping; a leopard (from its stripes) -- leopard. see HEBREW (H5247) Nimrah see HEBREW (H5249) Nimriym

column7: place of leopard, a place East of the Jordan
column9: From the same as (H5246) namer; clear water; Nimrah, a place East of the Jordan -- Nimrah. See also (H1039) Beyth Nimrah, (H5249) Nimriym. see HEBREW (H5246) namer see HEBREW (H1039) Beyth Nimrah see HEBREW (H5249) Nimriym

column7: a son of Cush and founder of the Bab. kingdom
column9: Or Nimrod {nim-rode'}; probably of foreign origin; Nimrod, a son of Cush -- Nimrod.

Plural of a masculine corresponding to (H5247) Nimrah; clear waters; Nimrim, a place East of the Jordan -- Nimrim. Compare (H1039) Beyth Nimrah. see HEBREW (H5247) Nimrah see HEBREW (H1039) Beyth Nimrah
Probably from (H4871) mashah; extricated; Nimshi, the (grand-)father of Jehu -- Nimshi. see HEBREW (H4871) mashah
From (H5264) nacac; a flag; also a sail; by implication, a flagstaff; generally a signal; figuratively, a token -- banner, pole, sail, (en-)sign, standard. see HEBREW (H5264) nacac
Feminine participle passive of (H5437) cabab; properly, an environment, i.e. Circumstance or turn of affairs -- cause. see HEBREW (H5437) cabab

column7: departing away, remove, take hold, turn away
column8: departing away, remove, take hold, turn away
column9: A primitive root; to retreat -- departing away, remove, take (hold), turn away.
A primitive root; to test; by implication, to attempt -- adventure, assay, prove, tempt, try.
A primitive root; to tear away -- destroy, pluck, root.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5255) nacach -- pull down. see HEBREW (H5255) nacach
From (H5258) nacak; properly, something poured out, i.e. A libation; also a molten image; by implication, a prince (as anointed) -- drink offering, duke, prince(-ipal). see HEBREW (H5258) nacak

column8: cover, melt, offer, cause to pour out, set up
column9: A primitive root; to pour out, especially a libation, or to cast (metal); by analogy, to anoint a king -- cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up).
A primitive root (probably identical with (H5258) nacak through the idea of fusion); to interweave, i.e. (figuratively) to overspread -- that is spread. see HEBREW (H5258) nacak
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5258) nacak; to pour out a libation -- offer. see HEBREW (H5258) nacak
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5262) necek; a libation -- drink offering. see HEBREW (H5262) necek
Or necek {nay'-sek}; from (H5258) nacak; a libation; also a cast idol -- cover, drink offering, molten image. see HEBREW (H5258) nacak
A primitive root; to wane, i.e. Be sick -- faint.

column7: perhaps to be high or conspicuous
column9: A primitive root; to gleam from afar, i.e. To be conspicuous as a signal; or rather perhaps a denominative from (H5251) nec (and identical with (H5263) nacac, through the idea of a flag as fluttering in the wind); to raise a beacon -- lift up as an ensign. see HEBREW (H5251) nec see HEBREW (H5263) nacac

column7: to pull out or up, set out, journey
column8: cause to blow, bring, get, make to go away, forth, forward, onward, out,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. Start on a journey -- cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), X still, be on his (go their) way.
A primitive root; to go up -- ascend.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5266) nacaq -- take up. see HEBREW (H5266) nacaq
Of foreign origin; Nisrok, a Babylonian idol -- Nisroch.
From (H5128) nuwa'; motion; Neah, a place in Palestine -- Neah. see HEBREW (H5128) nuwa'
From (H5128) nuwa'; movement; Noah, an Israelitess -- Noah. see HEBREW (H5128) nuwa'

Or naur {naw-oor'}; and (feminine) nturah {neh- oo-raw'}; properly, passive participle from (H5288) na'ar as denominative; (only in plural collectively or emphatic form) youth, the state (juvenility) or the persons (young people) -- childhood, youth. see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar
From (H5128) nuwa' and (H410) 'el; moved of God; Neiel, a place in Palestine -- Neiel. see HEBREW (H5128) nuwa' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H5276) na'em; delightful (objective or subjective, literal or figurative) -- pleasant(-ure), sweet. see HEBREW (H5276) na'em

column8: bolt, enclose, lock, shoe, shut up
column9: A primitive root; properly, to fasten up, i.e. With a bar or cord; hence (denominative from (H5275) na'al), to sandal, i.e. Furnish with slippers -- bolt, inclose, lock, shoe, shut up. see HEBREW (H5275) na'al

Or (feminine) na;alah {nah-al-aw'}; from (H5274) na'al; properly, a sandal tongue; by extens. A sandal or slipper (sometimes as a symbol of occupancy, a refusal to marry, or of something valueless) -- dryshod, (pair of) shoe((-latchet), -s). see HEBREW (H5274) na'al

column7: to be pleasant, delightful, or lovely
column8: pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet
column9: A primitive root; to be agreeable (literally or figuratively) -- pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet.
From (H5276) na'em; pleasure; Naam, an Israelite -- Naam. see HEBREW (H5276) na'em
From (H5276) na'em; agreeableness, i.e. Delight, suitableness, splendor or grace -- beauty, pleasant(-ness). see HEBREW (H5276) na'em

column4: proper name, feminine ; proper name, of a location
column7: a sister of Tubal-cain, also an Ammonitess
column9: Feminine of (H5277) Na'am; pleasantness; Naamah, the name of an antediluvian woman, of an Ammonitess, and of a place in Palestine -- Naamah. see HEBREW (H5277) Na'am
Patronymic from (H5283) Na'aman; a Naamanite, or descendant of Naaman (collectively) -- Naamites. see HEBREW (H5283) Na'aman
From (H5278) no'am; pleasant; Noomi, an Israelitess -- Naomi. see HEBREW (H5278) no'am
From (H5276) na'em; pleasantness (plural as concrete) -- pleasant. see HEBREW (H5276) na'em

column7: a descendant of Benjamin, also an Aramean (Syrian) general
column9: The same as (H5282) na'aman; Naaman, the name of an Israelite and of a Damascene -- Naaman. see HEBREW (H5282) na'aman
Patrial from a place corresponding in name (but not identical) with (H5279) Na'amah; a Naamathite, or inhabitant of Naamah -- Naamathite. see HEBREW (H5279) Na'amah
From an unused root meaning to prick; probably a brier; by implication, a thicket of thorny bushes -- thorn.
A primitive root; to growl -- yell.

column7: to shake, shake out or off
column8: shake off, out, self, overthrow, toss up and down
column9: A primitive root (probably identical with (H5286) na'ar, through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion's roar); to tumble about -- shake (off, out, self), overthrow, toss up and down. see HEBREW (H5286) na'ar

column8: babe, boy, child, damsel, lad, servant, young man
column9: From (H5287) na'ar; (concretely) a boy (as active), from the age of infancy to adolescence; by implication, a servant; also (by interch. Of sex), a girl (of similar latitude in age) -- babe, boy, child, damsel (from the margin), lad, servant, young (man). see HEBREW (H5287) na'ar
From (H5287) na'ar in its derivative sense of tossing about; a wanderer -- young one. see HEBREW (H5287) na'ar
From (H5287) na'ar; (abstractly) boyhood (compare (H5288) na'ar) -- child, youth. see HEBREW (H5287) na'ar see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar
Feminine of (H5288) na'ar; a girl (from infancy to adolescence) -- damsel, maid(-en), young (woman). see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, feminine
column7: an Israelite woman, also a place on the border of Ephraim
column9: The same as (H5291) na'arah; Naarah, the name of an Israelitess, and of a place in Palestine -- Naarah, Naarath. see HEBREW (H5291) na'arah
From (H5288) na'ar; youthful; Naarai, an Israelite -- Naarai. see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar
From (H5288) na'ar and (H3050) Yahh; servant of Jah; Nearjah, the name of two Israelites -- Neariah. see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H5288) na'ar; juvenile; Naaran, a place in Palestine -- Naaran. see HEBREW (H5288) na'ar
From (H5287) na'ar; something shaken out, i.e. Tow (as the refuse of flax) -- tow. see HEBREW (H5287) na'ar
A variation of (H4644) Moph; Noph, the capital of Upper Egypt -- Noph. see HEBREW (H4644) Moph
From an unused root probably meaning to spring forth; a sprout; Nepheg, the name of two Israelites -- Nepheg.
From (H5130) nuwph in the sense of lifting; a height; also a sieve -- border, coast, region, sieve. see HEBREW (H5130) nuwph
For (H5304) Nphiyciym; Nephushesim, a Temple- servant -- Nephisesim (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5304) Nphiyciym

column8: blow, breath, give up, cause to lose life, seething, snuff
column9: A primitive root; to puff, in various applications (literally, to inflate, blow hard, scatter, kindle, expire; figuratively, to disesteem) -- blow, breath, give up, cause to lose (life), seething, snuff.
From (H5301) naphach; a gust; Nophach, a place in Moab -- Nophah. see HEBREW (H5301) naphach

column7: giants, name of two peoples, one before the flood and one after the flood
column9: Or nphil {nef-eel'}; from (H5307) naphal; properly, a feller, i.e. A bully or tyrant -- giant. see HEBREW (H5307) naphal
Plural from an unused root meaning to scatter; expansions; Nephisim, a Temple-servant -- Nephusim (from the margin).
From (H5314) naphash; refreshed; Naphish, a son of Ishmael, and his posterity -- Naphish. see HEBREW (H5314) naphash
From an unused root meaning to glisten; shining; a gem, probably the garnet -- emerald.

column8: cast down, self, lots, out, cease, die, divide by lot, let fail,
column9: A primitive root; to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative) -- be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for (H6419) palal), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (X hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, X surely, throw down. see HEBREW (H6419) palal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5307) naphal -- fall (down), have occasion. see HEBREW (H5307) naphal
Or nephel {nay'-fel}; from (H5307) naphal; something fallen, i.e. An abortion -- untimely birth. see HEBREW (H5307) naphal

column8: be beaten in sunder, break in pieces, broken, dash in pieces, dispersed, be overspread, scatter
column9: A primitive root; to dash to pieces, or scatter -- be beaten in sunder, break (in pieces), broken, dash (in pieces), cause to be discharged, dispersed, be overspread, scatter.
From (H5310) naphats; a storm (as dispersing) -- scattering. see HEBREW (H5310) naphats

column7: to go or come out or forth
column9: (Aramaic) a primitive root; to issue; causatively, to bring out -- come (go, take) forth (out).
(Aramaic) from (H5312) nphaq; an outgo, i.e. Expense -- expense. see HEBREW (H5312) nphaq
A primitive root; to breathe; passively, to be breathed upon, i.e. (figuratively) refreshed (as if by a current of air) -- (be) refresh selves (-ed).

column7: a soul, living being, life, self, person, desire, passion, appetite, emotion
column8: any, thyself, them your-selves, slay, soul, tablet, they, thing,
column9: From (H5314) naphash; properly, a breathing creature, i.e. Animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental) -- any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, X dead(-ly), desire, X (dis-)contented, X fish, ghost, + greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, X jeopardy of) life (X in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure, (her-, him-, my-, thy-)self, them (your)-selves, + slay, soul, + tablet, they, thing, (X she) will, X would have it. see HEBREW (H5314) naphash

column7: height, a city belonging to Manasseh
column9: For (H5299) naphah; a height -- country. see HEBREW (H5299) naphah

column7: flowing honey, honey from the comb
column9: From (H5130) nuwph in the sense of shaking to pieces; a dripping i.e. Of honey (from the comb) -- honeycomb. see HEBREW (H5130) nuwph

column7: a place on the border of Judah and Benjamin
column9: From (H6605) pathach; opened, i.e. A spring; Nephtoach, a place in Palestine -- Neptoah. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6617) pathal; properly, wrestled; but ued (in the plural) transitively, a struggle -- wrestling. see HEBREW (H6617) pathal
Plural of foreign origin, Naphtuchim, an Egyptian tribe -- Naptuhim.

column4: proper name, masculine and of a tribe
column7: a son of Jacob, also his desc. and the district settled by them
column9: From (H6617) pathal; my wrestling; Naphtali, a son of Jacob, with the tribe descended from him, and its territory -- Naphtali. see HEBREW (H6617) pathal
From (H5340) natsats; a flower (from its brilliancy); also a hawk (from it flashing speed); --blossom, hawk. see HEBREW (H5340) natsats
A primitive root; to go away; --flee.

A prim root; to station, in various applications (literally or figuratively) -- appointed, deputy, erect, establish, X Huzzah (by mistake for a proper name), lay, officer, pillar, present, rear up, set (over, up), settle, sharpen, establish, (make to) stand(-ing, still, up, upright), best state.
Passive participle of (H5324) natsab; fixed, i.e. A handle -- haft. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5324) natsab; fixedness, i.e. Firmness -- strength. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab

column8: be laid waste, ruinous, strive together
column9: A primitive root; properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel -- be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).
Feminine of (H5322) nets; a blossom; --flower. see HEBREW (H5322) nets

column8: excel, chief musician singer, overseer, set forward
column9: A primitive root; properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. To be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); also (as denominative from (H5331) netsach), to be permanent -- excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward. see HEBREW (H5331) netsach
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5329) natsach; to become chief -- be preferred. see HEBREW (H5329) natsach

column8: always, constantly, end, nevermore, perpetual, strength, victory
column9: Or netsach {nay'-tsakh}; from (H5329) natsach; properly, a goal, i.e. The bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. To the most distant point of view); --alway(-s), constantly, end, (+ n-)ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory. see HEBREW (H5329) natsach
Probably identical with (H5331) netsach, through the idea of brilliancy of color; juice of the grape (as blood red) -- blood, strength. see HEBREW (H5331) netsach
Or ntsib {nets-eeb'}; from (H5324) natsab; something stationary, i.e. A prefect, a military post, a statue -- garrison, officer, pillar. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab
The same as (H5333) ntsiyb; station; Netsib, a place in Palestine -- Nezib. see HEBREW (H5333) ntsiyb

column7: head of a family of Nethinim
column9: From (H5329) natsach; conspicuous; Netsiach, a Temple- servant -- Neziah. see HEBREW (H5329) natsach
From (H5341) natsar; properly, conservative; but used passively, delivered -- preserved. see HEBREW (H5341) natsar

column7: to strip, plunder, deliver oneself, be delivered, snatch away, deliver
column8: to snatch away, at all, defend, deliver self, escape, without fail, part, pluck,
column9: A primitive root; to snatch away, whether in a good or a bad sense:- X at all, defend, deliver (self), escape, X without fail, part, pluck, preserve, recover, rescue, rid, save, spoil, strip, X surely, take (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5337) natsal; to extricate -- deliver, rescue. see HEBREW (H5337) natsal
From (H5322) nets; a blossom -- flower. see HEBREW (H5322) nets
A primitive root; to glare, i.e. Be bright- colored -- sparkle.

column8: besieged, hidden thing, keeper monument, observe, preserver,
column9: A primitive root; to guard, in a good sense (to protect, maintain, obey, etc.) Or a bad one (to conceal, etc.) -- besieged, hidden thing, keep(-er, -ing), monument, observe, preserve(-r), subtil, watcher(-man).
From (H5341) natsar in the sense of greenness as a striking color; a shoot; figuratively, a descendant -- branch. see HEBREW (H5341) natsar
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5352) naqah; clean -- pure. see HEBREW (H5352) naqah

column8: appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce,
column9: A primitive root; to puncture, literally (to perforate, with more or less violence) or figuratively (to specify, designate, libel) -- appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce, strike through.

column7: perhaps sockets (technical term of jeweler\'s work)
column9: A bezel (for a gem) -- pipe.
The same as (H5345) neqeb; dell; Nekeb, a place in Palestine -- Nekeb. see HEBREW (H5345) neqeb
From (H5344) naqab; female (from the sexual form) -- female. see HEBREW (H5344) naqab
From an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding); spotted -- speckled.

column7: sheep raiser, sheep dealer, sheep tender
column9: Active participle from the same as (H5348) naqod; a spotter (of sheep or cattle), i.e. The owner or tender (who thus marks them) -- herdman, sheepmaster. see HEBREW (H5348) naqod

column7: perhaps what is crumbled or easily crumbles, crumbs
column9: From the same as (H5348) naqod; a crumb (as broken to spots); also a biscuit (as pricked) -- cracknel, mouldy. see HEBREW (H5348) naqod
Feminine of (H5348) naqod; a boss -- stud. see HEBREW (H5348) naqod

column8: acquit at all, altogether, be blameless, cleanse, be clearing, cut off
column9: A primitive root; to be (or make) clean (literally or figuratively); by implication (in an adverse sense) to be bare, i.e. Extirpated -- acquit X at all, X altogether, be blameless, cleanse, (be) clear(-ing), cut off, be desolate, be free, be (hold) guiltless, be (hold) innocent, X by no means, be quit, be (leave) unpunished, X utterly, X wholly.

column7: head of a family of Nethinim
column9: Feminine of (H5348) naqod (in the figurative sense of marked); distinction; Nekoda, a Temple-servant -- Nekoda. see HEBREW (H5348) naqod
A primitive root; to loathe -- weary.

column8: blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent
column9: Or naqiyi (Joel (H4) 'eb: (H19) 'ibchah; Jonah (H1) 'ab: (H14) 'abah), {naw-kee'}; from (H5352) naqah; innocent -- blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent, quit. see HEBREW (H4) 'eb see HEBREW (H19) 'ibchah see HEBREW (H1) 'ab see HEBREW (H14) 'abah see HEBREW (H5352) naqah
Or niqqayon {nik-kaw-yone'}; from (H5352) naqah; clearness (literally or figuratively) -- cleanness, innocency. see HEBREW (H5352) naqah
From an unused root meaning to bore; a cleft -- hole.

column8: avenger, self, punish, revenge self, surely, take vengeance
column9: A primitive root; to grudge, i.e. Avenge or punish -- avenge(-r, self), punish, revenge (self), X surely, take vengeance.
From (H5358) naqam; revenge -- + avenged, quarrel, vengeance. see HEBREW (H5358) naqam
Feminine of (H5359) naqam; avengement, whether the act of the passion -- + avenge, revenge(-ing), vengeance. see HEBREW (H5359) naqam
A primitive root; to feel aversion -- be alienated.

column8: compass about cut down, destroy, go round about, enclose, round
column9: A primitive root; to strike with more or less violence (beat, fell, corrode); by implication (of attack) to knock together, i.e. Surround or circulate -- compass (about, -ing), cut down, destroy, go round (about), inclose, round.
From (H5362) naqaph; a threshing (of olives) -- shaking. see HEBREW (H5362) naqaph
From (H5362) naqaph; probably a rope (as encircling) -- rent. see HEBREW (H5362) naqaph

column8: dig, pick out, pierce, put thrust out
column9: A primitive root; to bore (penetrate, quarry) -- dig, pick out, pierce, put (thrust) out.
From (H5365) naqar, a fissure -- cleft, clift. see HEBREW (H5365) naqar

column7: to knock, strike, hit, strike or bring down
column9: A primitive root; to entrap (with a noose), literally or figuratively -- catch (lay a) snare.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5367) naqash; but used in the sense of (H5362) naqaph; to knock -- smote. see HEBREW (H5367) naqash see HEBREW (H5362) naqaph

column7: father of Abner, also the father of Kish
column9: The same as (H5216) niyr; lamp; Ner, an Israelite -- Ner. see HEBREW (H5216) niyr
Of foreign origin; Nergal, a Cuthite deity -- Nergal.
From (H5370) Nergal and (H8272) Shar'etser; Nergal-Sharetser, the name of two Babylonians -- Nergal-sharezer. see HEBREW (H5370) Nergal see HEBREW (H8272) Shar'etser
From an unused root meaning to roll to pieces; a slanderer -- talebearer, whisperer.
Of foreign origin; nard, an aromatic -- spikenard.

column7: lamp of Yah, father of Baruch
column9: Or Neriyahuw {nay-ree-yaw'-hoo}; from (H5216) niyr and (H3050) Yahh; light of Jah; Nerijah, an Israelite -- Neriah. see HEBREW (H5216) niyr see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: accept, advance, arise, able to, armor, suffer to bearer, up, bring forth,
column9: Or nacah (Psalm (H4) 'eb: (H6) 'abad ((H7) 'abad)) {naw-saw'}; a primitive root; to lift, in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, absol. And rel. (as follows) -- accept, advance, arise, (able to, (armor), suffer to) bear(-er, up), bring (forth), burn, carry (away), cast, contain, desire, ease, exact, exalt (self), extol, fetch, forgive, furnish, further, give, go on, help, high, hold up, honorable (+ man), lade, lay, lift (self) up, lofty, marry, magnify, X needs, obtain, pardon, raise (up), receive, regard, respect, set (up), spare, stir up, + swear, take (away, up), X utterly, wear, yield. see HEBREW (H4) 'eb see HEBREW (H6) 'abad see HEBREW (H7) 'abad
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5375) nasa' -- carry away, make insurrection, take. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'

column7: to lend on interest, be a creditor
column9: A primitive root; to lead astray, i.e. (mentally) to delude, or (morally) to seduce -- beguile, deceive, X greatly, X utterly.

A primitive root (perhaps identical with (H5377) nasha', through the idea of imposition); to lend on interest; by implication, to dun for debt -- X debt, exact, giver of usury. see HEBREW (H5377) nasha'
Passive participle feminine of (H5375) nasa'; something taken, i.e. A present -- gift. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
A primitive root; to blow; by implication, to disperse -- (cause to) blow, drive away.

column8: ability, be able, attain unto, be able to, can get, lay at, put, reach,
column9: A primitive root; to reach (literally or figuratively) -- ability, be able, attain (unto), (be able to, can) get, lay at, put, reach, remove, wax rich, X surely, (over-)take (hold of, on, upon).
A primitive root; to forget; figuratively, to neglect; causatively, to remit, remove -- forget, deprive, exact.

column8: creditor, exact, extortioner, lend, usurer, lend on taker on usury
column9: A primitive root (rather identical with (H5382) nashah, in the sense of (H5378) nasha'); to lend or (by reciprocity) borrow on security or interest -- creditor, exact, extortioner, lend, usurer, lend on (taker on) usury. see HEBREW (H5382) nashah see HEBREW (H5378) nasha'

column7: a vein (or nerve) in the thigh
column9: From (H5382) nashah, in the sense of failure; rheumatic or crippled (from the incident to Jacob) -- which shrank. see HEBREW (H5382) nashah
Or rather, nsutah {nes-oo-aw'}; feminine. Passive participle of (H5375) nasa'; something borne, i.e. A load -- carriage. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
From (H5383) nashah; a debt -- debt. see HEBREW (H5383) nashah

column7: one lifted up, a chief, prince
column8: captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapor
column9: Or nasi' {naw-see'}; from (H5375) nasa'; properly, an exalted one, i.e. A king or sheik; also a rising mist -- captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapour. see HEBREW (Hnasi8) #NAME? see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
From (H5382) nashah; oblivion; --forgetfulness. see HEBREW (H5382) nashah
(Aramaic) irregular plural feminine of (H606) 'enash -- women. see HEBREW (H606) 'enash
From (H5401) nashaq; a kiss -- kiss. see HEBREW (H5401) nashaq
A primitive root; to strike with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to oppress with interest on a loan -- bite, lend upon usury.
From (H5391) nashak; interest on a debt -- usury. see HEBREW (H5391) nashak
For (H3957) lishkah; a cell -- chamber. see HEBREW (H3957) lishkah

column7: to slip or drop off, draw off, clear away
column8: cast out, drive, loose, put off out, slip
column9: A primitive root; to pluck off, i.e. Divest, eject or drop -- cast (out), drive, loose, put off (out), slip.
A primitive root; properly, to blow away, i.e. Destroy -- destroy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5397) nshamah; vital breath -- breath. see HEBREW (H5397) nshamah

column8: blast, that breaths, inspiration, soul, spirit
column9: From (H5395) nasham; a puff, i.e. Wind, angry or vital breath, divine inspiration, intellect. Or (concretely) an animal -- blast, (that) breath(-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit. see HEBREW (H5395) nasham
A primitive root; to breeze, i.e. Blow up fresh (as the wind) -- blow.

column8: dark, dawning of the day morning, night, twilight
column9: From (H5398) nashaph; properly, a breeze, i.e. (by implication) dusk (when the evening breeze prevails) -- dark, dawning of the day (morning), night, twilight. see HEBREW (H5398) nashaph
A primitive root; to catch fire -- burn, kindle.

column8: armed men, rule, kiss, that touched
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H5400) nasaq, through the idea of fastening up; compare (H2388) chazaq, (H2836) chashaq); to kiss, literally or figuratively (touch); also (as a mode of attachment), to equip with weapons -- armed (men), rule, kiss, that touched. see HEBREW (H5400) nasaq see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq see HEBREW (H2836) chashaq

column8: armed men, armoury, battle, harness, weapon
column9: Or nesheq {nay'-shek}; from (H5401) nashaq; military equipment, i.e. (collectively) arms (offensive or defensive), or (concretely) an arsenal -- armed men, armour(-y), battle, harness, weapon. see HEBREW (H5401) nashaq
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5404) nesher; an eagle -- eagle. see HEBREW (H5404) nesher
From an unused root meaning to lacerate; the eagle (or other large bird of prey) -- eagle.
A primitive root; properly, to eliminate, i.e. (intransitively) to dry up -- fail.
Probably of Persian origin; an epistle -- letter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5406) nishtvan -- letter. see HEBREW (H5406) nishtvan

column7: to cut up, cut in pieces, divide by joints
column8: cut in pieces, divide, hew in pieces
column9: A primitive root; to dismember -- cut (in pieces), divide, hew in pieces.
From (H5408) nathach; a fragment -- part, piece. see HEBREW (H5408) nathach
Or (feminine) nthiybah {neth-ee-baw'}; or nthibah (Jeremiah 6:16) {neth-ee-baw'}; from an unused root meaning to tramp; a (beaten) track -- path((-way)), X travel(-ler), way.

Or Nathuwn (Ezra 8:17) {naw-thoon'} (the proper form as passive participle), from (H5414) nathan; one given, i.e. (in the plural only) the Nethinim, or Temple-servants (as given to that duty) -- Nethinims. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5411) Nathiyn -- Nethinims. see HEBREW (H5411) Nathiyn

column7: to pour forth, be poured out
column8: drop, gather together, melt, pour forth, out
column9: A primitive root; to flow forth (literally or figuratively); by implication, to liquify -- drop, gather (together), melt, pour (forth, out).

column8: add, apply, appoint, ascribe, assign, avenge, be healed, bestow,
column9: A primitive root; to give, used with greatest latitude of application (put, make, etc.) -- add, apply, appoint, ascribe, assign, X avenge, X be ((healed)), bestow, bring (forth, hither), cast, cause, charge, come, commit, consider, count, + cry, deliver (up), direct, distribute, do, X doubtless, X without fail, fasten, frame, X get, give (forth, over, up), grant, hang (up), X have, X indeed, lay (unto charge, up), (give) leave, lend, let (out), + lie, lift up, make, + O that, occupy, offer, ordain, pay, perform, place, pour, print, X pull, put (forth), recompense, render, requite, restore, send (out), set (forth), shew, shoot forth (up), + sing, + slander, strike, (sub-)mit, suffer, X surely, X take, thrust, trade, turn, utter, + weep, + willingly, + withdraw, + would (to) God, yield.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5414) nathan; give -- bestow, give pay. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: From (H5414) nathan; given; Nathan, the name of five Israelites -- Nathan. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan

column7: given of God, the name of a number of Isr
column9: From (H5414) nathan and (H410) 'el; given of God; Nethanel, the name of ten Israelites -- Nethaneel. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: given of Yah, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Nthanyahuw {neth-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H5414) nathan and (H3050) Yahh; given of Jah; Nethanjah, the name of four Israelites -- Nethaniah. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: given of a king, a leader in Judah
column9: From (H5414) nathan and (H4428) melek; given of (the) king; Nethan-Melek, an Israelite -- Nathan-melech. see HEBREW (H5414) nathan see HEBREW (H4428) melek
A primitive root; to tear up -- mar.

column7: to break, break down, or out
column9: For (H5422) nathats; to tear out -- break. see HEBREW (H5422) nathats

column8: beat down, break down out, cast down, destroy, overthrow, pull down, throw down
column9: A primitive root; to tear down -- beat down, break down (out), cast down, destroy, overthrow, pull down, throw down.

column7: to pull, draw, or tear away, apart, or off
column8: break off, burst, draw away, lift up, pluck away, off, pull out, root out
column9: A primitive root; to tear off -- break (off), burst, draw (away), lift up, pluck (away, off), pull (out), root out.
From (H5423) nathaq; scurf -- (dry) scall. see HEBREW (H5423) nathaq

column8: drive asunder, leap, let loose, make, move, undo
column9: A primitive root; to jump, i.e. Be violently agitated; causatively, to terrify, shake off, untie -- drive asunder, leap, (let) loose, X make, move, undo.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5425) nathar -- shake off. see HEBREW (H5425) nathar
From (H5425) nathar; mineral potash (so called from effervescing with acid) -- nitre. see HEBREW (H5425) nathar

column7: to pull or pluck up, root out
column8: destroy, forsake, pluck out, up, by the roots, pull up, root out up, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to tear away -- destroy, forsake, pluck (out, up, by the roots), pull up, root out (up), X utterly.

column7: seah (a measure of flour or grain)
column9: From an unused root meaning to define; a seah, or certain measure (as determinative) for grain -- measure.
From (H5431) ca'an; perhaps a military boot (as a protection from mud -- battle. see HEBREW (H5431) ca'an
A primitive root; to be miry; used only as denominative from (H5430) c'own; to shoe, i.e. (active participle) a soldier shod -- warrior. see HEBREW (H5430) c'own
For (H5429) c'ah; measurement, i.e. Moderation -- measure. see HEBREW (H5429) c'ah
A primitive root; to quaff to satiety, i.e. Become tipsy -- drunkard, fill self, Sabean, (wine-)bibber.

column7: son of Cush, also his desc. and their land
column9: Of foreign origin; Seba, a son of Cush, and the country settled by him -- Seba.
From (H5433) caba'; potation, concretely (wine), or abstractly (carousal) -- drink, drunken, wine. see HEBREW (H5433) caba'
Patrial from (H5434) Cba'; a Sebaite, or inhabitant of Seba -- Sabean. see HEBREW (H5434) Cba'

column7: to turn about, go around, surround
column8: bring, cast, fetch, lead, make, walk, whirl, round about,
column9: A primitive root; to revolve, surround, or border; used in various applications, literally and figuratively (as follows) -- bring, cast, fetch, lead, make, walk, X whirl, X round about, be about on every side, apply, avoid, beset (about), besiege, bring again, carry (about), change, cause to come about, X circuit, (fetch a) compass (about, round), drive, environ, X on every side, beset (close, come, compass, go, stand) round about, inclose, remove, return, set, sit down, turn (self) (about, aside, away, back).
From (H5437) cabab; a (providential) turn (of affairs) -- cause. see HEBREW (H5437) cabab

column4: substantive; adverb; preposition; substantive; adverb accusative; preposition; substantive; preposition
column8: place, round about, circuit, compass, on every side
column9: Or (feminine) cbiybah {seb-ee-baw'}; from (H5437) cabab; (as noun) a circle, neighbour, or environs; but chiefly (as adverb, with or without preposition) around -- (place, round) about, circuit, compass, on every side. see HEBREW (H5437) cabab
A primitive root; to entwine -- fold together, wrap.
From (H5440) cabak; a copse -- thicket. see HEBREW (H5440) cabak
From (H5440) cabak, a copse -- thick(-et). see HEBREW (H5440) cabak
(Aramaic) or sabbka: (Aramaic) {sab-bek- aw'}; from a root corresponding to (H5440) cabak; a lyre -- sackbut. see HEBREW (H5440) cabak
From (H5440) cabak; copse-like; Sibbecai, an Israelite -- Sibbecai, Sibbechai. see HEBREW (H5440) cabak

column8: bear, be a burden, carry, strong to labor
column9: A primitive root; to carry (literally or figuratively), or (reflexively) be burdensome; specifically, to be gravid -- bear, be a burden, carry, strong to labour.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5445) cabal; to erect -- strongly laid. see HEBREW (H5445) cabal
From (H5445) cabal; a load (literally or figuratively) -- burden, charge. see HEBREW (H5445) cabal
(only in the form cubbal {soob-bawl'}; from (H5445) cabal; a load (figuratively) -- burden. see HEBREW (H5445) cabal
From (H5445) cabal; a porter -- (to bear, bearer of) burden(-s). see HEBREW (H5445) cabal
From (H5447) cebel; porterage -- burden. see HEBREW (H5447) cebel
For (H7641) shibbol; an ear of grain -- Sibboleth. see HEBREW (H7641) shibbol
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to bear in mind, i.e. Hope -- think.
Dual from a root corresponding to (H5452) cbar; double hope; Sibrajim, a place in Syria -- Sibraim. see HEBREW (H5452) cbar

column7: a son of Cush, also the territory settled by his desc
column9: Or Cabtah {sab-taw'}; probably of foreign derivation; Sabta or Sabtah, the name of a son of Cush, and the country occupied by his posterity -- Sabta, Sabtah.

column7: a son of Cush, also the territory settled by his desc
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Sabteca, the name of a son of Cush, and the region settled by him -- Sabtecha, Sabtechah.
A primitive root; to prostrate oneself (in homage) -- fall down.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5456) cagad -- worship. see HEBREW (H5456) cagad
From (H5462) cagar; properly, shut up, i.e. The breast (as inclosing the heart); also gold (as generally shut up safely) -- caul, gold. see HEBREW (H5462) cagar

column8: jewel, peculiar treasure, proper good, special
column9: Feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to shut up; wealth (as closely shut up) -- jewel, peculiar (treasure), proper good, special.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5461) cagan -- governor. see HEBREW (H5461) cagan
From an unused root meaning to superintend; a prefect of a province -- prince, ruler.

column8: close up, deliver up, give over up, enclose, pure, repair, shut in, self,
column9: A primitive root; to shut up; figuratively, to surrender -- close up, deliver (up), give over (up), inclose, X pure, repair, shut (in, self, out, up, up together), stop, X straitly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5462) cagar -- shut up. see HEBREW (H5462) cagar
Probably from (H5462) cagar in the sense of sweeping away; a pouring rain -- very rainy. see HEBREW (H5462) cagar
From an unused root meaning to estop; the stocks -- stocks.
From an unused root meaning to envelop; a wrapper, i.e. Shirt -- fine linen, sheet.

column7: a Canaanite city near the Dead Sea
column9: From an unused root meaning to scorch; burnt (i.e. Volcanic or bituminous) district; Sedom, a place near the Dead Sea -- Sodom.
From an unused root meaning to arrange; order -- order.
From an unused root meaning to be round; roundness -- round.
From the same as (H5469) cahar; a dungeon (as surrounded by walls) -- prison. see HEBREW (H5469) cahar
Of foreign derivation; So, an Egyptian king -- So.

column8: backslider, drive, go back, turn away, back
column9: A primitive root; properly, to flinch, i.e. (by implication) to go back, literally (to retreat) or figuratively (to apostatize) -- backslider, drive, go back, turn (away, back).

A primitive root (probably rather identical with (H5472) cuwg through the idea of shrinking from a hedge; compare (H7735) suwg); to hem in, i.e. Bind -- set about. see HEBREW (H5472) cuwg see HEBREW (H7735) suwg
From (H5462) cagar; an inclosure, i.e. Cage (for an animal) -- ward. see HEBREW (H5462) cagar

From (H3245) yacad; a session, i.e. Company of persons (in close deliberation); by implication, intimacy, consultation, a secret -- assembly, consel, inward, secret (counsel). see HEBREW (H3245) yacad
From (H5475) cowd; a confidant; Sodi, an Israelite -- Sodi. see HEBREW (H5475) cowd
From an unused root meaning to wipe away; sweeping; Suach, an Israelite -- Suah.
From the same as (H5477) Cuwach; something swept away, i.e. Filth -- torn. see HEBREW (H5477) Cuwach
From (H7750) suwt; roving; Sotai, one of the Nethinim -- Sotai. see HEBREW (H7750) suwt
A primitive root; properly, to smear over (with oil), i.e. Anoint -- anoint (self), X at all.
(Aramaic) or cuwmponyah (Aramaic) {soom-po-neh-yaw'}; or ciyphonya: (Dan. 3:10) (Aramaic) {see-fo-neh-yaw'}; of Greek origin; a bagpipe (with a double pipe) -- dulcimer.

column7: a city on the S. border of Egypt
column9: (rather to be written Cvenah {sev-ay'-naw}; for Cven {sev-ane'}; i.e to Seven); of Egyptian derivation; Seven, a place in Upper Egypt -- Syene.

Or cuc {soos}; from an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy); a horse (as leaping); also a swallow (from its rapid flight) -- crane, horse((-back, -hoof)). Compare (H6571) parash. see HEBREW (H6571) parash
Feminine of (H5483) cuwc; a mare -- company of horses. see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc
From (H5483) cuwc; horse-like; Susi, an Israelite -- Susi. see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc

column7: to come to an end, cease
column8: consume, have an end, perish, be utterly
column9: A primitive root; to snatch away, i.e. Terminate -- consume, have an end, perish, X be utterly.
