(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5486) cuwph; to come to an end -- consume, fulfill. see HEBREW (H5486) cuwph
Probably of Egyptian origin; a reed, especially the papyrus -- flag, Red (sea), weed. Compare (H5489) Cuwph. see HEBREW (H5489) Cuwph

column7: reed, a place near which the law was given
column9: For (H5488) cuwph (by ellipsis of (H3220) yam); the Reed (Sea) -- Red Sea. see HEBREW (H5488) cuwph see HEBREW (H3220) yam
From (H5486) cuwph; a termination -- conclusion, end, hinder participle see HEBREW (H5486) cuwph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5490) cowph -- end. see HEBREW (H5490) cowph

column4: noun feminine; proper name, of a location
column8: Red Sea, storm, tempest, whirlwind, Red sea
column9: From (H5486) cuwph; a hurricane -- Red Sea, storm, tempest, whirlwind, Red sea. see HEBREW (H5486) cuwph

column8: behead, bring, call back, decline, depart, eschew, get you, go aside,
column9: Or suwr (Hosea 9:12) {soor}; a primitive root; to turn off (literal or figurative) -- be(-head), bring, call back, decline, depart, eschew, get (you), go (aside), X grievous, lay away (by), leave undone, be past, pluck away, put (away, down), rebel, remove (to and fro), revolt, X be sour, take (away, off), turn (aside, away, in), withdraw, be without.
Probably passive participle of (H5493) cuwr; turned off, i.e. Deteriorated -- degenerate. see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr

column7: a turning aside, a gate of the temple
column9: The same as (H5494) cuwr; Sur, a gate of the temple -- Sur. see HEBREW (H5494) cuwr

column8: entice, move, persuade, provoke, remove, set on, stir up, take away
column9: Perhaps denominative from (H7898) shayith; properly, to prick, i.e. (figuratively) stimulate; by implication, to seduce -- entice, move, persuade, provoke, remove, set on, stir up, take away. see HEBREW (H7898) shayith
Probably from the same root as (H4533) macveh; covering, i.e. Clothing -- clothes. see HEBREW (H4533) macveh
A primitive root; to trail along -- draw (out), tear.
From (H5498) cachab; a rag -- cast clout. see HEBREW (H5498) cachab
A primitive root; to sweep away -- scrape.
From (H5500) cachah; refuse (as swept off) -- offscouring. see HEBREW (H5500) cachah
A primitive root; to scrape off -- sweep (away).

column7: to go around or about, travel about
column8: go about, merchantman, occupy with, pant, trade, traffic
column9: A primitive root; to travel round (specifically as a pedlar); intensively, to palpitate -- go about, merchant(-man), occupy with, pant, trade, traffick.
From (H5503) cachar; profit (from trade) -- merchandise. see HEBREW (H5503) cachar
From (H5503) cachar; an emporium; abstractly, profit (from trade) -- mart, merchandise. see HEBREW (H5503) cachar
From (H5503) cachar: traffic -- merchandise. see HEBREW (H5503) cachar
Properly, active participle feminine of (H5503) cachar; something surrounding the person, i.e. A shield -- buckler. see HEBREW (H5503) cachar
Similar to (H5507) cocherah; probably a (black) tile (or tessara) for laying borders with -- black marble. see HEBREW (H5507) cocherah

column7: a moving back or away, dross
column9: Or cuwg (Ezek. 22:18) {soog}; from (H5472) cuwg in the sense of refuse; scoria -- dross. see HEBREW (H5472) cuwg

column7: third month of the Jewish year
column9: Probably of Persian origin; Sivan, the third Heb. Month -- Sivan.
Or Ciychon {see-khone'}; from the same as (H5477) Cuwach; tempestuous; Sichon, an Amoritish king -- Sihon. see HEBREW (H5477) Cuwach
Of uncertain derivation; Sin the name of an Egyptian town and (probably) desert adjoining -- Sin.
From an otherwise unknown name of a man; a Sinite, or descendant of one of the sons of Canaan -- Sinite.

column7: the mountain where the law was given
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Sinai, mountain of Arabia -- Sinai.
Plural of an otherwise unknown name; Sinim, a distant Oriental region -- Sinim.

column7: a general of the king of Hazor, also the father of some returning exiles
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Sisera, the name of a Canaanitish king and of one of the Nethinim -- Sisera.
Or Ciyeahai {see-ah-haw'}; from an unused root meaning to converse; congregation; Sia or Siaha, one of the Nethinim -- Sia, Siaha.

Or (feminine) ciyrah {see-raw'}; or cirah (Jeremiah 52:18) {see-raw'}; from a primitive root meaning to boil up; a pot; also a thorn (as springing up rapidly); by implication, a hook -- caldron, fishhook, pan, ((wash-))pot, thorn.
From (H5526) cakak; properly, a thicket of men, i.e. A crowd -- multitude. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak
From (H5526) cakak; a hut (as of entwined boughs); also a lair -- covert, den, pavilion, tabernacle. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak

column8: booth, cottage, covert, pavilion, tabernacle, tent
column9: Fem of (H5520) cok; a hut or lair -- booth, cottage, covert, pavilion, tabernacle, tent. see HEBREW (H5520) cok
Feminine of (H5519) cak; an (idolatrous) booth -- tabernacle. see HEBREW (H5519) cak

column7: a city East of the Jordan, also a place in Egypt
column9: Or Cukkoth {sook-kohth'}; plural of (H5521) cukkah; booths; Succoth, the name of a place in Egypt and of three in Palestine -- Succoth. see HEBREW (H5521) cukkah

column7: booths of daughters, an Assyr.-Bab. god
column9: From (H5523) Cukkowth and the (irreg.) Plural of (H1323) bath; booths of (the) daughters; brothels, i.e. Idoalatrous tents for impure purpose -- Succoth-benoth. see HEBREW (H5523) Cukkowth see HEBREW (H1323) bath
Patrial from an unknown name (perhaps (H5520) cok); a Sukkite, or inhabitant of some place near Egypt (i.e. Hut-dwellers) -- Sukkiims. see HEBREW (H5520) cok

column8: cover, defense, defend, hedge in, join together, set, shut up
column9: Or sakak (Exod. 33:22) {saw-kak'}; a primitive root; properly, to entwine as a screen; by implication, to fence in, cover over, (figuratively) protect -- cover, defence, defend, hedge in, join together, set, shut up.
From (H5526) cakak; inclosure; Secacah, a place in Palestine -- Secacah. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak

column7: to be foolish or a fool
column9: For (H3688) kacal; to be silly -- do (make, play the, turn into) fool(-ish, -ishly, -ishness). see HEBREW (H3688) kacal
From (H5528) cakal; silliness; concretely and collectively, dolts -- folly. see HEBREW (H5528) cakal
From (H5528) cakal; silly -- fool(-ish), sottish. see HEBREW (H5528) cakal
Or sikluwth (Eccl. 1:17) {sik-looth'}; from (H5528) cakal; silliness -- folly, foolishness. see HEBREW (H5528) cakal

column7: to be of use or service, benefit
column8: acquaint self, be advantage, ever, be, unprofitable, treasurer, be wont
column9: A primitive root; to be familiar with; by implication, to minister to, be serviceable to, be customary -- acquaint (self), be advantage, X ever, (be, (un-))profit(-able), treasurer, be wont.
Probably a denominative from (H7915) sakkiyn; properly, to cut, i.e. Damage; also to grow (causatively, make) poor -- endanger, impoverish. see HEBREW (H7915) sakkiyn
A primitive root; to shut up; by implication, to surrender -- stop, give over. See also (H5462) cagar, (H7936) sakar. see HEBREW (H5462) cagar see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
A primitive root to be silent; by implication, to observe quietly -- take heed.
From (H5549) calal; properly, a willow twig (as pendulous), i.e. An osier; but only as woven into a basket -- basket. see HEBREW (H5549) calal
A primitive root; to suspend in a balance, i.e. Weigh -- compare.
From (H5549) calal; an embankment; Silla, a place in Jerusalem -- Silla. see HEBREW (H5549) calal
A primitive root; probably to leap (with joy), i.e. Exult -- harden self.
From (H5539) calad; exultation; Seled, an Israelite -- Seled. see HEBREW (H5539) calad

column7: to make light of, toss aside
column9: A primitive root; to hang up, i.e. Weigh, or (figuratively) contemn -- tread down (under foot), value.
From (H5541) calah; suspension (of music), i.e. Pause -- Selah. see HEBREW (H5541) calah
Or Calluw; {sal-loo'}; or Caluw {sal-loo'}; or Callay {sal-lah'-ee}; from (H5541) calah; weighed; Sallu or Sallai, the name of two Israelites -- Sallai, Sallu, Salu. see HEBREW (H5541) calah
Or callown {sal-one'}; from (H5541) calah; a prickle (as if pendulous); brier, thorn. see HEBREW (H5541) calah
A primitive root; to forgive -- forgive, pardon, spare.
From (H5545) calach; placable: ready to forgive. see HEBREW (H5545) calach
From (H5545) calach; pardon -- forgiveness, pardon. see HEBREW (H5545) calach

column7: a city on the E. border of Bashan
column9: From an unused root. Meaning to walk; walking; Salcah, a place East of the Jordan -- Salcah, Salchah.

column8: cast up, exalt self, extol, make plain, raise up
column9: A primitive root; to mound up (especially a turnpike); figurative, to exalt; reflexively, to oppose (as by a dam) -- cast up, exalt (self), extol, make plain, raise up.
Or cowllah {so-lel-aw'}; active participle feminine of (H5549) calal, but used passively; a military mound, i.e. Rampart of besiegers -- bank, mount. see HEBREW (H5549) calal
From (H5549) calal; a stair-case -- ladder. see HEBREW (H5549) calal
From (H5541) calah; a twig (as pendulous) -- basket. see HEBREW (H5541) calah
From an unused root meaning to be lofty; a craggy rock, literally or figuratively (a fortress) -- (ragged) rock, stone(-ny), strong hold.
The same as (H5553) cela'; Sela, the rock-city of Idumaea -- rock, Sela(-h). see HEBREW (H5553) cela'

From (H5553) cela' and the plural of (H4256) machaloqeth with the article interposed; rock of the divisions; Sela- ham-Machlekoth, a place in Palestine -- Sela-hammalekoth. see HEBREW (H5553) cela' see HEBREW (H4256) machaloqeth
Apparently from the same as (H5553) cela' in the sense of crushing as with a rock, i.e. Consuming; a kind of locust (from its destructiveness) -- bald locust. see HEBREW (H5553) cela'
A primitive root; properly, to wrench, i.e. (figuratively) to subvert -- overthrow, pervert.
From (H5557) calaph; distortion, i.e. (figuratively) viciousness -- perverseness. see HEBREW (H5557) calaph
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to ascend -- come (up).
From an unused root meaning to strip; flour (as chipped off) -- (fine) flour, meal.
From an unused root meaning to smell sweet; an aroma -- sweet (spice).
Of foreign origin; Samgar-Nebo, a Babylonian general -- Samgar-nebo.
Of uncertain derivation; a vine blossom; used also adverbially, abloom -- tender grape.

column8: bear up, establish, uphold, lay, lean, lie hard, put, rest self,
column9: A primitive root; to prop (literally or figuratively); reflexively, to lean upon or take hold of (in a favorable or unfavorable sense) -- bear up, establish, (up-)hold, lay, lean, lie hard, put, rest self, set self, stand fast, stay (self), sustain.
From (H5564) camak and (H3050) Yahh; supported of Jah; Semakjah, an Israelite -- Semachiah. see HEBREW (H5564) camak see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or cemel {say'-mel}; from an unused root meaning to resemble; a likeness -- figure, idol, image.
A primitive root; to designate -- appointed.
A primitive root; to be erect, i.e. Bristle as hair -- stand up, tremble.
From (H5568) camar; bristling, i.e. Shaggy -- rough. see HEBREW (H5568) camar
From an unused root meaning to prick; thorny; Senaah, a place in Palestine -- Senaah, Hassenaah (with the article).
Of foreign origin; Sanballat, a Persian satrap of Samaria -- Sanballat.
From an unused root meaning to prick; a bramble -- bush.
The same s (H5572) cnah; thorn; Seneh, a crag in Palestine -- Seneh. see HEBREW (H5572) cnah

Or Cnu.ah {sen-oo-aw'} from the same as (H5570) Cna'ah; pointed; (used with the article as a proper name) Senuah, the name of two Israelites -- Hasenuah (including the art), Senuah. see HEBREW (H5570) Cna'ah
Of uncertain derivation; (in plural) blindness -- blindness.
Of foreign origin; Sancherib, an Assyrian king -- Sennacherib.
From an unused root meaning to be pointed; a twig (as tapering) -- bough.
Feminine of a form of (H5577) cancin; a bough; Sansannah, a place in Palestine -- Sansannah. see HEBREW (H5577) cancin
Of uncertain derivation; a fin (collectively) -- fins.
From the same as (H5483) cuwc; a moth (from the agility of the fly) -- moth. see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc
Of uncertain derivation; Sismai, an Israelite -- Sisamai.

column8: comfort, establish, hold up, refresh self, strengthen, be upholden
column9: A primitive root; to suport (mostly figurative) -- comfort, establish, hold up, refresh self, strengthen, be upholden.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5582) ca'ad; to aid -- helping. see HEBREW (H5582) ca'ad
A primitive root; to rush -- storm.
From (H5586) ca'aph; a fissure (of rocks); also a bough (as subdivided) -- (outmost) branch, clift, top. see HEBREW (H5586) ca'aph
A primitive root; properly, to divide up; but used only as denominative from (H5585) ca'iyph, to disbranch (a tree) -- top. see HEBREW (H5585) ca'iyph
Or samiph {saw-eef'}; from (H5586) ca'aph; divided (in mind), i.e. (abstractly) a sentiment -- opinion. see HEBREW (H5586) ca'aph
From (H5586) ca'aph; divided (in mind), i.e. (concretely) a skeptic -- thought. see HEBREW (H5586) ca'aph
Feminine of (H5585) ca'iyph; a twig -- bough, branch. Compare (H5634) car'appah. see HEBREW (H5585) ca'iyph see HEBREW (H5634) car'appah

column8: be toss with tempestuous, be sore, troubled, scatter with a whirlwind
column9: A primitive root; to rush upon; by implication, to toss (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative) -- be (toss with) tempest(-uous), be sore, troubled, come out as a (drive with the, scatter with a) whirlwind.
Or (feminine) ctarah {seh-aw-raw'}; from (H5590) ca'ar; a hurricane -- storm(-y), tempest, whirlwind. see HEBREW (H5590) ca'ar

column8: bason, bowl, cup, door post, gate, post, threshold
column9: From (H5605) caphaph, in its original sense of containing; a vestibule (as a limit); also a dish (for holding blood or wine) -- bason, bowl, cup, door (post), gate, post, threshold. see HEBREW (H5605) caphaph
The same as (H5592) caph; Saph, a Philistine -- Saph. Compare (H5598) Cippay. see HEBREW (H5592) caph see HEBREW (H5598) Cippay
A primitive root; properly, to tear the hair and beat the breasts (as Orientals do in grief); generally to lament; by implication, to wail -- lament, mourn(-er), wail.

column7: to sweep or snatch away, catch up
column8: add, augment, consume, destroy, heap, join, perish, put
column9: A primitive root; properly, to scrape (literally, to shave; but usually figuratively) together (i.e. To accumulate or increase) or away (i.e. To scatter, remove, or ruin; intransitively, to perish) -- add, augment, consume, destroy, heap, join, perish, put.

column8: abiding, gather together, cleave, smite with the scab
column9: Or saphach (Isaiah 3:17) {saw-fakh'}; a primitive root; properly, to scrape out, but in certain peculiar senses (of removal or association) -- abiding, gather together, cleave, smite with the scab.
From (H5596) caphach; the mange (as making the hair fall off) -- scab. see HEBREW (H5596) caphach
From (H5592) caph; bason-like; Sippai, a Philistine -- Sippai. Compare (H5593) Caph. see HEBREW (H5592) caph see HEBREW (H5593) Caph

column8: such things as which grow of themselves, which grows of its own accord
column9: From (H5596) caphach; something (spontaneously) falling off, i.e. A self-sown crop; figuratively, a freshet -- (such) things as (which) grow (of themselves), which groweth of its own accord (itself). see HEBREW (H5596) caphach
From (H5603) caphan; a (sea-going) vessel (as ceiled with a deck) -- ship. see HEBREW (H5603) caphan
From (H5608) caphar; a gem (perhaps used for scratching other substances), probably the sapphire -- sapphire. see HEBREW (H5608) caphar
From an unused root meaning to depress; a basin (as deepened out) -- bowl, dish.
A primitive root; to hide by covering; specifically, to roof (passive participle as noun, a roof) or wainscot; figuratively, to reserve -- cieled, cover, seated.
From (H5603) caphan; a wainscot -- cieling. see HEBREW (H5603) caphan

column7: to stand at or guard the threshold
column9: A primitive root; properly, to snatch away, i.e. Terminate; but used only as denominative from (H5592) caph (in the sense of a vestibule), to wait at the threshold -- be a doorkeeper. see HEBREW (H5592) caph

Or saphaq (1 Kings 20:10; Job 27:23; Isaiah 2:6) {saw-fak'}; a primitive root; to clap the hands (in token of compact, derision, grief, indignation, or punishment); by implication of satisfaction, to be enough; by implication of excess, to vomit -- clap, smite, strike, suffice, wallow.
Or sepheq (Job 20:22; job 36:18) {seh'-fek}; from (H5606) caphaq; chastisement; also satiety -- stroke, sufficiency. see HEBREW (H5606) caphaq

column8: commune, account; declare, number, penknife, reckon, scribe, show forth, speak,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to score with a mark as a tally or record, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe, and also to enumerate; intensively, to recount, i.e. Celebrate -- commune, (ac-)count; declare, number, + penknife, reckon, scribe, shew forth, speak, talk, tell (out), writer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5608) caphar; a book -- book, roll. see HEBREW (H5608) caphar
From (H5608) caphar; a census -- numbering. see HEBREW (H5608) caphar
The same as (H5610) cphar; Sephar, a place in Arabia -- Sephar. see HEBREW (H5610) cphar

column8: bill, book, evidence, learned letter, register, scroll
column9: Or (feminine) ciphrah (Psa. 56:8; Psa. 56:9) {sif-raw'}; from (H5608) caphar; properly, writing (the art or a document); by implication, a book -- bill, book, evidence, X learn(-ed) (-ing), letter, register, scroll. see HEBREW (H9) 'abedah see HEBREW (H5608) caphar
(Aramaic) from the same as (H5609) cphar; a scribe (secular or sacred) -- scribe. see HEBREW (H5609) cphar
Of foreign derivation; Sepharad, a region of Assyria -- Sepharad.
From (H5608) caphar; a numeration -- number. see HEBREW (H5608) caphar
Patrial from (H5617) Cpharvayim; a Sepharvite or inhabitant of Sepharvain -- Sepharvite. see HEBREW (H5617) Cpharvayim

column7: a city conquered by the king of Assyr
column9: (dual)
Feminine active participle of (H5608) caphar; a scribe (properly, female); Sophereth, a temple servant -- Sophereth. see HEBREW (H5608) caphar

column7: to stone, put to death by stoning
column8: cast, gather out, throw stones, surely
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be weighty; but used only in the sense of lapidation or its contrary (as if a delapidation) -- (cast, gather out, throw) stone(-s), X surely.
Contracted from (H5637) carar; peevish -- heavy, sad. see HEBREW (H5637) carar
From an unused root meaning to sting; a thistle -- brier.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a cloak -- coat.
Of foreign derivation; Sargon, an Assyrian king -- Sargon.
From a primitive root meaning to tremble; trembling; Sered, an Israelite -- Sered.
Patron from (H5624) Cered; a Seredite (collectively) or descendants of Sered -- Sardites. see HEBREW (H5624) Cered
From (H5493) cuwr; departure; Sirah, a cistern so-called -- Sirah. See also (H5518) ciyr. see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr see HEBREW (H5518) ciyr

column8: continual, rebellion, revolted, turn away, wrong
column9: From (H5493) cuwr; apostasy, crime; figuratively, remission -- X continual, rebellion, revolt((-ed)), turn away, wrong. see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr

column7: to go free, be unrestrained, overrun, exceed
column8: exceeding, hand, spread, stretch self, banish
column9: A primitive root; to extend (even to excess) -- exceeding, hand, spread, stretch self, banish.
From (H5628) carach; a redundancy -- remnant. see HEBREW (H5628) carach
For (H8302) shiryown; a coat of mail -- brigandine. see HEBREW (H8302) shiryown

Or caric {saw-reece'}; from an unused root meaning to castrate; a eunuch; by implication, valet (especially of the female apartments), and thus, a minister of state -- chamberlain, eunuch, officer. Compare (H7249) Rab-Cariyc. see HEBREW (H7249) Rab-Cariyc
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; an emir -- president.
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; an axle; figuratively, a peer -- lord, plate.
For (H5589) c'appah; a twig -- bough. see HEBREW (H5589) c'appah
A primitive root; to cremate, i.e. To be (near) of kin (such being privileged to kindle the pyre) -- burn.
From (H5635) caraph; a nettle (as stinging like a burn) -- brier. see HEBREW (H5635) caraph

column8: away, backsliding, rebellious, revolting, slide back, stubborn, withdrew
column9: A primitive root; to turn away, i.e. (morally) be refractory -- X away, backsliding, rebellious, revolter(-ing), slide back, stubborn, withdrew.
From an unused root meaning to hide; winter (as the dark season) -- winter.
From (H5641) cathar; hidden; Sethur, an Israelite -- Sethur. see HEBREW (H5641) cathar

column7: to stop up, shut up, keep close
column8: closed up, hidden, secret, shut out up, stop
column9: Or satham (Numbers 24:15) {saw-tham'}; a primitive root; to stop up; by implication, to repair; figuratively, to keep secret -- closed up, hidden, secret, shut out (up), stop.

column8: be absent, keep close, conceal, hide self, keep secret, surely
column9: A primitive root; to hide (by covering), literally or figuratively -- be absent, keep close, conceal, hide (self), (keep) secret, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5641) cathar; to conceal; figuratively, to demolish -- destroy, secret thing. see HEBREW (H5641) cathar

column8: backbiting, covering, covert, disguise, hiding place, protection, secretly,
column9: Or (feminine) cithrah (Deut. 32:38), {sith-raw'}; from (H5641) cathar; a cover (in a good or a bad, a literal or a figurative sense) -- backbiting, covering, covert, X disguise(-th), hiding place, privily, protection, secret(-ly, place). see HEBREW (H5641) cathar
From (H5643) cether; protective; Sithri, an Israelite,: see HEBREW (H5643) cether

(masculine and feminine); from (H5743) uwb; properly, an envelope, i.e. Darkness (or density, 2 Chron. 4:17); specifically, a (scud) cloud; also a copse -- clay, (thick) cloud, X thick, thicket. Compare (H5672) abiy. see HEBREW (H5743) uwb see HEBREW (H5672) abiy

Or sob {obe}; from an unused root meaning to cover; properly, equivalent to (H5645) ab; but used only as an architectural term, an architrave (as shading the pillars) -- thick (beam, plant). see HEBREW (H5645) ab

column8: keep in bondage, be bondmen, bond-service, compel, do, dress, ear,
column9: A primitive root; to work (in any sense); by implication, to serve, till, (causatively) enslave, etc. -- X be, keep in bondage, be bondmen, bond-service, compel, do, dress, ear, execute, + husbandman, keep, labour(-ing man, bring to pass, (cause to, make to) serve(-ing, self), (be, become) servant(-s), do (use) service, till(-er), transgress (from margin), (set a) work, be wrought, worshipper,

column8: cut, do, execute, go on, make, move, work
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H5647) abad; to do, make, prepare, keep, etc. -- X cut, do, execute, go on, make, move, work. see HEBREW (H5647) abad
(Aramaic) from (H5648) abad; a servant -- servant. see HEBREW (H5648) abad
From (H5647) abad; a servant -- X bondage, bondman, (bond-)servant, (man-)servant. see HEBREW (H5647) abad
The same as (H5650) ebed; Ebed, the name of two Israelites -- Ebed. see HEBREW (H5650) ebed
From (H5647) abad; a deed -- work. see HEBREW (H5647) abad
From (H5647) abad; work; Abda, the name of two Israelites -- Abda see HEBREW (H5647) abad

column7: servant of Edom, an Israelite name
column8: Obed-Edom, the name of five Israelites
column9: From the active participle of (H5647) abad and (H123) 'Edom; worker of Edom; Obed-Edom, the name of five Israelites: see HEBREW (H5647) abad see HEBREW (H123) 'Edom

column7: servant of God, a man of Judah
column9: From (H5647) abad and (H410) 'el; serving God; Abdeel, an Israelite: Abdeel. Compare (H5661) Abdiy'el. see HEBREW (H5647) abad see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5661) Abdiy'el

column8: act, bondage, bondservant, effect, labor, ministering, office, service, tillage,

Passive participle of (H5647) abad; something wrought, i.e. (concretely) service -- household, store of servants. see HEBREW (H5647) abad

column4: proper name; proper name, masculine ; proper name, of a location; proper name, of a people; proper name, masculine or of a people; proper name, of a mountain

From (H5647) abad; servitude -- bondage. see HEBREW (H5647) abad
From (H5647) abad; serviceable; Abdi, the name of two Israelites -- Abdi. see HEBREW (H5647) abad
From (H5650) ebed and (H410) 'el; servant of God; Abdiel, an Israelite -- Abdiel. Compare (H5655) Abd'el. see HEBREW (H5650) ebed see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5655) Abd'el

column7: servant of Yah, the name of a number of Isr

column7: servant of a king, an official under King Zedekiah
column9: From (H5650) ebed and (H4428) melek; servant of a king; Ebed-Melek, a eunuch of Zedekeah -- Ebed-melech. see HEBREW (H5650) ebed see HEBREW (H4428) melek

column7: servant of Nebo, Bab. name of one of Daniel\'s companions
column9: (Aramaic) of foreign origin; Abed-Nego, the name of Azariah -- Abed-nego.

column9: From (H5670) abat; something pledged, i.e. (collectively) pawned goods -- thick clay (by a false etym.). see HEBREW (H5670) abat
Or mobiy {ob-ee'}; from (H5666) abah; density, i.e. Depth or width -- thick(-ness). Compare (H5645) ab. see HEBREW (H5666) abah see HEBREW (H5645) ab
(Aramaic) from (H5648) abad; labor or business -- affairs, service, work. see HEBREW (H5648) abad

column7: to pass over, through, or by, pass on

From (H5674) abar; a crossing-place -- ferry, plain (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5674) abar

column4: Adjective and name of a people; noun

column9: Patronymic from (H5677) Eber; an Eberite (i.e. Hebrew) or descendant of Eber -- Hebrew(-ess, woman). see HEBREW (H5677) Eber
The same as (H5680) Ibriy; Ibri, an Israelite -- Ibri. see HEBREW (H5680) Ibriy

From (H5676) eber; transitional; Ebron, a place in Palestine -- Hebron. Perhaps a clerical error for (H5658) Abdown. see HEBREW (H5676) eber see HEBREW (H5658) Abdown
Feminine of (H5683) Ebron; Ebronah, place in the Desert -- Ebronah. see HEBREW (H5683) Ebron
A primitive root; to dry up -- be rotten.
A primitive root; to interlace, i.e. (figuratively) to pervert -- wrap up.
Or rabowth {aw-both'}; from (H5686) abath; intwined, i.e. Dense -- thick. see HEBREW (H5686) abath

A primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. To love (sensually) -- dote, lover.
From (H5689) agab; love (concretely), i.e. Amative words -- much love, very lovely. see HEBREW (H5689) agab
From (H5689) agab; love (abstractly), i.e. Amorousness -- inordinate love. see HEBREW (H5689) agab

column9: From (H5746) uwg; an ash-cake (as round) -- cake (upon the hearth). see HEBREW (H5746) uwg

From the same as (H5696) agol; a (male) calf (as frisking round), especially one nearly grown (i.e. A steer) -- bullock, calf. see HEBREW (H5696) agol
Or magowl {aw-gole'}; from an unused root meaning to revolve, circular -- round.
Feminine of (H5695) egel; a (female) calf, especially one nearly grown (i.e. A heifer) -- calf, cow, heifer. see HEBREW (H5695) egel
The same as (H5697) eglah; Eglah, a wife of David -- Eglah. see HEBREW (H5697) eglah
From the same as (H5696) agol; something revolving, i.e. A wheeled vehicle -- cart, chariot, wagon see HEBREW (H5696) agol

column7: a king of Moab, also a city in Isr
column9: From (H5695) egel; vituline; Eglon, the name of a place in Palestine and of a Moabitish king -- Eglon. see HEBREW (H5695) egel
A primitive root; to be sad -- grieve.

column7: to shut oneself in or off
column9: A primitive root; to debar, i.e. From marriage -- stay.

column9: From (H5710) adah; properly, a (peremptory) terminus, i.e. (by implication) duration, in the sense of advance or perpetuity (substantially as a noun, either with or without a preposition) -- eternity, ever(- lasting, -more), old, perpetually, + world without end. see HEBREW (H5710) adah

column7: as far as, even to, up to, until, while
column8: against, and, as, at, before, by that, even to, forasmuch as,
column9: Properly, the same as (H5703) ad (used as a preposition, adverb or conjunction; especially with a preposition); as far (or long, or much) as, whether of space (even unto) or time (during, while, until) or degree (equally with) -- against, and, as, at, before, by (that), even (to), for(-asmuch as), (hither-)to, + how long, into, as long (much) as, (so) that, till, toward, until, when, while, (+ as) yet. see HEBREW (H5703) ad
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5704) ad; X and, at, for, (hither-)to, on till, (un-)to, until, within. see HEBREW (H5704) ad
The same as (H5703) ad in the sense of the aim of an attack; booty -- prey. see HEBREW (H5703) ad
Contracted from (H5749) uwd; concretely, a witness; abstractly, testimony; specifically, a recorder, i.e. Prince -- witness. see HEBREW (H5749) uwd

From an unused root meaning to set a period (compare (H5710) adah, (H5749) uwd); the menstrual flux (as periodical); by implication (in plural) soiling -- filthy. see HEBREW (H5710) adah see HEBREW (H5749) uwd

column8: alter, depart, pass away, remove, take away
column9: (Aramaic) or adah (Aramaic) {ad-aw'}; corresponding to (H5710) adah -- alter, depart, pass (away), remove, take (away). see HEBREW (H5710) adah

column8: adorn, deck self, pass by, take away
column9: A primitive root; to advance, i.e. Pass on or continue; causatively, to remove; specifically, to bedeck (i.e. Bring an ornament upon) -- adorn, deck (self), pass by, take away.
From (H5710) adah; ornament; Adah, the name of two women -- Adah. see HEBREW (H5710) adah

Feminine of (H5707) ed in its techn. Sense; testimony -- testimony, witness. Compare (H5712) edah. see HEBREW (H5707) ed see HEBREW (H5712) edah

Feminine of (H5707) ed; testimony -- testimony, witness. see HEBREW (H5707) ed
From (H5710) adah in the sense of trappings; finery; generally an outfit; specifically, a headstall -- X excellent, mouth, ornament. see HEBREW (H5710) adah

column7: God is an ornament, three Israelites
column9: From (H5716) adiy and (H410) 'el; ornament of God; Adiel, the name of three Israelites -- Adiel. see HEBREW (H5716) adiy see HEBREW (H410) 'el

The same as (H5719) adiyn; Adin, the name of two Israelites -- Adin. see HEBREW (H5719) adiyn
From (H5719) adiyn; effeminacy; Adina, an Israelite -- Adina. see HEBREW (H5719) adiyn
Probably from (H5719) adiyn in the original sense of slender (i.e. A spear); his spear -- Adino. see HEBREW (H5719) adiyn
Dual of a feminine of (H5706) ad; double prey; Adithajim, a place in Palestine -- Adithaim. see HEBREW (H5706) ad
Probably from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Adlai, an Israelite -- Adlai.
Probably from the passive participle of the same as (H5724) Adlay; Adullam, a place in Palestine -- Adullam. see HEBREW (H5724) Adlay
Patrial from (H5725) Adullam; an Adullamite or native of Adullam -- Adullamite. see HEBREW (H5725) Adullam
A primitive root; to be soft or pleasant; figuratively and reflexively, to live voluptuously -- delight self.
Or radennah {ad-en'-naw}; from (H5704) ad and (H2004) hen; till now -- yet. see HEBREW (H5704) ad see HEBREW (H2004) hen
From (H5727) adan; pleasure; Eden, a place in Mesopotamia -- Eden. see HEBREW (H5727) adan
Or (feminine) aednah {ed-naw'}; from (H5727) adan; pleasure -- delicate, delight, pleasure. See also (H1040) Beyth 'Eden. see HEBREW (H5727) adan see HEBREW (H1040) Beyth 'Eden

column7: the garden home of Adam and Eve
column9: The same as (H5730) eden (masculine); Eden, the region of Adam's home -- Eden. see HEBREW (H5730) eden
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of (H5708) ed; a set time; technically, a year -- time. see HEBREW (H5708) ed
From (H5727) adan; pleasure; Adna, the name of two Israelites -- Adna. see HEBREW (H5727) adan
From (H5727) adan; pleasure; Adnah, the name of two Israelites -- Adnah. see HEBREW (H5727) adan
From (H5712) edah; festival; Adadah, a place in Palestine -- Adadah. see HEBREW (H5712) edah

column7: to remain over, be in excess
column8: be more, odd number, be have over and above, remain
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, have) redundant -- be more, odd number, be (have) over (and above), overplus, remain.
A primitive root; to arrange, as a battle, a vineyard (to hoe); hence, to muster and so to miss (or find wanting) -- dig, fail, keep (rank), lack.
From (H5737) adar; an arrangement (i.e. Drove); Eder, an Israelite -- Ader. see HEBREW (H5737) adar
From (H5737) adar; an arrangement, i.e. Muster (of animals) -- drove, flock, herd. see HEBREW (H5737) adar

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column9: The same as (H5739) eder; Eder, the name of an Israelite and of two places in Palestine -- Edar, Eder. see HEBREW (H5739) eder

column7: my help is God, son-in-law of Saul
column9: From (H5739) eder and (H410) 'el; flock of God; Adriel, an Israelite -- Adriel. see HEBREW (H5739) eder see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a lentil -- lentile.
A primitive root; to be dense or dark, i.e. To becloud -- cover with a cloud.

column7: worshiper, the name of several Israelites
column9: Active participle of (H5647) abad; serving; Obed, the name of five Israelites -- Obed. see HEBREW (H5647) abad

column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc
column9: Of foreign derivation; Obal, a son of Joktan -- Obal.
A primitive root; properly, to gyrate; but used only as a denominative from (H5692) uggah, to bake (round cakes on the hearth) -- bake. see HEBREW (H5692) uggah
Probably from (H5746) uwg; round; Og, a king of Bashan -- Og. see HEBREW (H5746) uwg

column7: (a reed musical instrument) perhaps a flute
column9: Or buggab {oog-gawb'}; from (H5689) agab in the original sense of breathing; a reed-instrument of music -- organ. see HEBREW (H5689) agab

column7: to return, go about, repeat, do again
column8: admonish, charge, earnestly, lift up, protest, call take to record, relieve, rob,
column9: A primitive root; to duplicate or repeat; by implication, to protest, testify (as by reiteration); intensively, to encompass, restore (as a sort of reduplication) -- admonish, charge, earnestly, lift up, protest, call (take) to record, relieve, rob, solemnly, stand upright, testify, give warning, (bear, call to, give, take to) witness.

column7: a going around, continuance, still, yet, again, beside
column8: again, all life long, at all, besides, but, else, furthermore, henceforth,
column9: Or rod {ode}; from (H5749) uwd; properly, iteration or continuance; used only adverbially (with or without preposition), again, repeatedly, still, more -- again, X all life long, at all, besides, but, else, further(-more), henceforth, (any) longer, (any) more(-over), X once, since, (be) still, when, (good, the) while (having being), (as, because, whether, while) yet (within). see HEBREW (H5749) uwd
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5750) owd -- while. see HEBREW (H5750) owd
Or moded {o-dade'}; from (H5749) uwd; reiteration; Oded, the name of two Israelites -- Oded. see HEBREW (H5749) uwd

column8: do amiss, bow down, make crooked, commit iniquity, pervert, do perversely, trouble, turn,
column9: A primitive root; to crook, literally or figuratively (as follows) -- do amiss, bow down, make crooked, commit iniquity, pervert, (do) perverse(-ly), trouble, X turn, do wickedly, do wrong.
Intensive from (H5753) avah abbreviated; overthrow -- X overturn. see HEBREW (H5753) avah
Or eavvae (2 Kings 17:24) {av-vaw'}; for (H5754) avvah; Ivvah or Avva, a region of Assyria -- Ava, Ivah. see HEBREW (H5754) avvah

column8: gather self, self to flee, retire
column9: A primitive root; to be strong; causatively, to stregthen, i.e. (figuratively) to save (by flight) -- gather (self, self to flee), retire.
Patrial from (H5755) Ivvah; an Avvite or native of Avvah (only plural) -- Avims, Avites. see HEBREW (H5755) Ivvah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5753) avah; perverseness -- iniquity. see HEBREW (H5753) avah
From (H5764) uwl; a babe -- young child, little one. see HEBREW (H5764) uwl
From (H5765) aval; perverse (morally) -- ungodly. see HEBREW (H5765) aval

column7: a city in Benjamin, also a people on the S.W. coast of the Mediterranean Sea
column9: Plural of (H5757) Avviy; Avvim (as inhabited by Avvites), a place in Palestine (with the article prefix) -- Avim. see HEBREW (H5757) Avviy

Or (perhaps Ayowth {ah-yoth'}, as if plural of (H5857) Ay) cayuwth {ah-yoth'}; from (H5753) avah; ruin; Avvith (or Avvoth), a place in Palestine -- Avith. see HEBREW (H5857) Ay see HEBREW (H5753) avah
A primitive root; to suckle, i.e. Give milk -- milch, (ewe great) with young.
From (H5763) uwl; a babe -- sucking child, infant. see HEBREW (H5763) uwl
A primitive root; to distort (morally) -- deal unjustly, unrighteous.

column5: evel or avel or avlah or olah
column9: Or lavel {aw'-vel}; and (feminine) lavlah {av-law'}; or owlah {o-law'}; or.olah {o-law'}; from (H5765) aval; (moral) evil -- iniquity, perverseness, unjust(-ly), unrighteousness(-ly); wicked(-ness). see HEBREW (H5765) aval
Intensive from (H5765) aval; evil (morally) -- unjust, unrighteous, wicked. see HEBREW (H5765) aval

column8: babe, young child, infant, little one
column9: Or lolal {o-lawl'}; from (H5763) uwl; a suckling -- babe, (young) child, infant, little one. see HEBREW (H5763) uwl

column8: always, ancient time, any more, continuance, eternal, for, everlasting, long time,
column9: Or lolam {o-lawm'}; from (H5956) alam; properly, concealed, i.e. The vanishing point; generally, time out of mind (past or future), i.e. (practically) eternity; frequentatively, adverbial (especially with prepositional prefix) always -- alway(-s), ancient (time), any more, continuance, eternal, (for, (n-))ever(-lasting, -more, of old), lasting, long (time), (of) old (time), perpetual, at any time, (beginning of the) world (+ without end). Compare (H5331) netsach, (H5703) ad. see HEBREW (H5956) alam see HEBREW (H5331) netsach see HEBREW (H5703) ad
Denominative from (H5869) ayin; to watch (with jealosy) -- eye. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin

column8: fault, iniquity, mischief, punishment of iniquity, sin
column9: Or oavown (2 Kings 7:9; Psalm 51:5; Psalm 51:7) {aw-vone'}; from (H5753) avah; perversity, i.e. (moral) evil -- fault, iniquity, mischeif, punishment (of iniquity), sin. see HEBREW (H7) 'abad see HEBREW (H5753) avah
From an unused root apparently meaning to dwell together; sexual (cohabitation) -- duty of marriage.
From (H5753) avah; perversity -- X perverse. see HEBREW (H5753) avah

column8: brandish, be wax faint, flee away, fly away, set, shine forth, weary
column9: A primitive root; to cover (with wings or obscurity); hence (as denominative from (H5775) owph) to fly; also (by implication of dimness) to faint (from the darkness of swooning) -- brandish, be (wax) faint, flee away, fly (away), X set, shine forth, weary. see HEBREW (H5775) owph
From (H5774) uwph; a bird (as covered with feathers, or rather as covering with wings), often collectively -- bird, that flieth, flying, fowl. see HEBREW (H5774) uwph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5775) owph -- fowl. see HEBREW (H5775) owph
Or mophereth {o-feh'-reth}; feminine participle active of (H6080) aphar; lead (from its dusty color) -- lead. see HEBREW (H6080) aphar
From (H5775) owph; birdlike; Ephai, an Israelite -- Ephai (from margin). see HEBREW (H5775) owph
A primitive root; to consult -- take advice ((counsel) together).

column7: a son of Aram, also a son of Nahor, also an Edomite, also perhaps a district East of Pal
column9: Apparently from (H5779) uwts; consultation; Uts, a son of Aram, also a Seirite, and the regions settled by them. -- Uz. see HEBREW (H5779) uwts
A primitive root; to pack -- be pressed.

column8: awaken, up, lift up self, master, raise up, stir up self
column9: A primitive root (rather identical with (H5783) uwr through the idea of opening the eyes); to wake (literally or figuratively) -- (a-)wake(-n, up), lift up (self), X master, raise (up), stir up (self). see HEBREW (H5783) uwr
A primitive root; to (be) bare -- be made naked.
(Aramaic) chaff (as the naked husk) -- chaff.
From (H5783) uwr; skin (as naked); by implication, hide, leather -- hide, leather, skin. see HEBREW (H5783) uwr
A primitive root (rather denominatively from (H5785) owr through the idea of a film over the eyes); to blind -- blind, put out. See also (H5895) ayir. see HEBREW (H5785) owr see HEBREW (H5895) ayir
Intensive from (H5786) avar; blind (literally or figuratively) -- blind (men, people). see HEBREW (H5786) avar
And (feminine) avvereth {av-veh'-reth}; from (H5787) ivver; blindness -- blind(-ness). see HEBREW (H5787) ivver

column7: to lend aid, come to help
column9: A primitive root; to hasten -- assemble self.
For (H5789) uwsh; to hasten, i.e. Succor -- speak in season. see HEBREW (H5789) uwsh
A primitive root; to wrest -- bow self, (make) crooked., falsifying, overthrow, deal perversely, pervert, subvert, turn upside down.
From (H5791) avath; oppression -- wrong. see HEBREW (H5791) avath
From (H5790) uwth; succoring; Uthai, the name of two Israelites -- Uthai. see HEBREW (H5790) uwth

column8: fierce, greedy, mighty, power, roughly, strong
column9: From (H5810) azaz; strong, vehement, harsh -- fierce, + greedy, mighty, power, roughly, strong. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
From (H5810) azaz; a she-goat (as strong), but masculine in plural (which also is used ellipt. For goat's hair) -- (she) goat, kid. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5795) ez -- goat. see HEBREW (H5795) ez

column8: boldness, loud, might, power, strength, strong
column9: Or (fully) rowz {oze}; from (H5810) azaz; strength in various applications (force, security, majesty, praise) -- boldness, loud, might, power, strength, strong. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, masculine
column9: Or (Uzzah {ooz-zaw'}; feminine of (H5797) oz; strength; Uzza or Uzzah, the name of five Israelites -- Uzza, Uzzah. see HEBREW (H5797) oz
From (H5795) ez and (H235) 'azal; goat of departure; the scapegoat -- scapegoat. see HEBREW (H5795) ez see HEBREW (H235) 'azal

column8: commit self, fail, forsake, fortify, help, leave destitute, off, refuse,
column9: A primitive root; to loosen, i.e. Relinquish, permit, etc. -- commit self, fail, forsake, fortify, help, leave (destitute, off), refuse, X surely.
From (H5800) azab in the sense of letting go (for a price, i.e. Selling); trade, i.e. The place (mart) or the payment (revenue) -- fair, ware. see HEBREW (H5800) azab
From (H5794) az and the root of (H950) buwqah; stern depopulator; Azbuk, an Israelite -- Azbuk. see HEBREW (H5794) az see HEBREW (H950) buwqah

column7: Gad is mighty, an Israelite name
column9: From (H5794) az and (H1409) gad; stern troop; Azgad, an Israelite -- Azgad. see HEBREW (H5794) az see HEBREW (H1409) gad
Feminine of (H5794) az; strong; Azzah, a place in Palestine -- Azzah, Gaza. see HEBREW (H5794) az
Feminine passive participle of (H5800) azab; desertion (of inhabitants) -- forsaking. see HEBREW (H5800) azab
The same as (H5805) azuwbah; Azubah, the name of two Israelitesses -- Azubah. see HEBREW (H5805) azuwbah
From (H5810) azaz; forcibleness -- might, strength. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
From (H5810) azaz; forcible; collectively and concretely, an army -- power, strong. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
Or mazzur {az-zoor'}; from (H5826) azar; helpful; Azzur, the name of three Israelites -- Azur, Azzur. see HEBREW (H5826) azar

column8: harden, impudent, prevail, strengthen self, be strong
column9: A primitive root; to be stout (literally or figuratively) -- harden, impudent, prevail, strengthen (self), be strong.
From (H5810) azaz; strong; Azaz, an Israelite -- Azaz. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
From (H5810) azaz and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has strengthened; Azazjah, the name of three Israelites -- Azaziah. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: forceful, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H5810) azaz; forceful; Uzzi, the name of six Israelites -- Uzzi. see HEBREW (H5810) azaz
Perhaps for (H5818) Uzziyah; Uzzija, an Israelite -- Uzzia. see HEBREW (H5818) Uzziyah
From (H5756) uwz and (H410) 'el; strengthened of God; Aziel, an Israelite -- Aziel. Compare (H3268) Ya'aziy'el. see HEBREW (H5756) uwz see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3268) Ya'aziy'el

column7: my strength is God, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H5797) oz and (H410) 'el; strength of God; Uzziel, the name of six Israelites -- Uzziel. see HEBREW (H5797) oz see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H5816) Uzziy'el; an Uzzielite (collectively) or descendants of Uzziel -- Uzzielites. see HEBREW (H5816) Uzziy'el

column7: my strength is Yah, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Uzziyahuw {ooz-zee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H5797) oz and (H3050) Yahh; strength of Jah; Uzzijah, the name of five Israelites -- Uzziah. see HEBREW (H5797) oz see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H5756) uwz; strengthfulness; Aziza, an Israelite -- Aziza. see HEBREW (H5756) uwz

From (H5794) az and (H4194) maveth; strong one of death; Azmaveth, the name of three Israelites and of a place in Palestine -- Azmaveth. See also (H1041) Beyth 'Azmaveth. see HEBREW (H5794) az see HEBREW (H4194) maveth see HEBREW (H1041) Beyth 'Azmaveth
From (H5794) az; strong one; Azzan, an Israelite -- Azzan. see HEBREW (H5794) az
Probably feminine of (H5797) oz; probably the sea-eagle (from its strength) -- ospray. see HEBREW (H5797) oz
A primitive root; to grub over -- fence about.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5823) azaq; a signet-ring (as engraved) -- signet. see HEBREW (H5823) azaq
From (H5823) azaq; tilled; Azekah, a place in Palestine -- Azekah. see HEBREW (H5823) azaq
A primitive root; to surround, i.e. Protect or aid -- help, succour.
From (H5826) azar; help; Ezer, the name of two Israelites -- Ezer. Compare (H5829) Ezer. see HEBREW (H5826) azar see HEBREW (H5829) Ezer
From (H5826) azar; aid -- help. see HEBREW (H5826) azar
The same as (H5828) ezer; Ezer, the name of four Israelites -- Ezer. Compare (H5827) Ezer. see HEBREW (H5828) ezer see HEBREW (H5827) Ezer
A variation of (H5833) ezrah; Ezra, an Israelite -- Ezra. see HEBREW (H5833) ezrah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5830) Ezra'; Ezra, an Israelite --Ezra. see HEBREW (H5830) Ezra'

column7: God has helped, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H5826) azar and (H410) 'el; God has helped; Azarel, the name of five Israelites -- Azarael, Azareel. see HEBREW (H5826) azar see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or mezrath (Psa. 60:11; Psa. 60:13; Psa. 108:12; Psa. 108:13) {ez-rawth'}; feminine of (H5828) ezer; aid -- help(-ed, -er). see HEBREW (H13) 'obdan see HEBREW (H13) 'obdan see HEBREW (H5828) ezer
The same as (H5833) ezrah; Ezrah, an Israelite -- Ezrah. see HEBREW (H5833) ezrah
From (H5826) azar in its original meaning of surrounding; an inclosure; also a border -- court, settle. see HEBREW (H5826) azar
From (H5828) ezer; helpful; Ezri, an Israelite -- Ezri. see HEBREW (H5828) ezer

column7: my help is God, three Israelites
column9: From (H5828) ezer and (H410) 'el; help of God; Azriel, the name of three Israelites -- Azriel. see HEBREW (H5828) ezer see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column9: Or mazaryahuw {az-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H5826) azar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has helped; Azarjah, the name of nineteen Israelites -- Azariah. see HEBREW (H5826) azar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5838) Azaryah; Azarjah, one of Daniel's companions -- Azariah. see HEBREW (H5838) Azaryah

column7: my help has risen, four Israelites
column9: From (H5828) ezer and active participle of (H6965) quwm; help of an enemy; Azrikam, the name of four Israelites -- Azrikam. see HEBREW (H5828) ezer see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
Patrial from (H5804) Azzah; an Azzathite or inhabitant of Azzah -- Gazathite, Gazite. see HEBREW (H5804) Azzah
From (H5860) iyt (contracted) in the sense of swooping, i.e. Side-long stroke; a stylus or marking stick -- pen. see HEBREW (H5860) iyt
(Aramaic) from (H3272) y'at,; prudence -- counsel. see HEBREW (H3272) y'at,

column7: to wrap oneself, enwrap, envelop oneself
column8: array self, be clad, put a cover self, fill, put on, surely, turn aside
column9: A primitive root; to wrap, i.e. Cover, veil, cloth, or roll -- array self, be clad, (put a) cover (-ing, self), fill, put on, X surely, turn aside.
From an unused root meaning apparently to contain; a receptacle (for milk, i.e. Pail; figuratively, breast) -- breast.
From an unused root meaning to sneeze; sneezing -- sneezing.
Of uncertain derivation; a bat -- bat.

column8: cover over, fail, faint, feebler, hide self, be overwhelmed, swoon
column9: A primitive root; to shroud, i.e. Clothe (whether transitive or reflex.); hence (from the idea of darkness) to languish -- cover (over), fail, faint, feebler, hide self, be overwhelmed, swoon.
A primitive root; to encircle (for attack or protection); especially to crown (literally or figuratively) -- compass, crown.
From (H5849) atar; a crown -- crown. see HEBREW (H5849) atar
The same as (H5850) atarah; Atarah, an Israelitess -- Atarah. see HEBREW (H5850) atarah

column7: the name of several places in Isr
column9: Or Ataroth {at-aw-roth'}; plural of (H5850) atarah; Ataroth, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine -- Ataroth. see HEBREW (H5850) atarah

column7: a place on the border between Ephraim and Benjamin
column9: From the same as (H5852) Atarowth and (H146) 'Addar; crowns of Addar; Atroth-Addar, a place in Palestine -- Ataroth-adar(-addar). see HEBREW (H5852) Atarowth see HEBREW (H146) 'Addar

From the same as (H5852) Atarowth and (H1004) bayith and (H3097) Yow'ab; crowns of the house of Joab; Atroth-beth-Joab, a place in Palestine -- Ataroth the house of Joab. see HEBREW (H5852) Atarowth see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H3097) Yow'ab

column8: Atroth, Shophan as if two places
column9: From the same as (H5852) Atarowth and a name otherwise unused (being from the same as (H8226) saphan) meaning hidden; crowns of Shophan; Atroth-Shophan, a place in Palestine -- Atroth, Shophan (as if two places). see HEBREW (H5852) Atarowth see HEBREW (H8226) saphan
From (H5753) avah; a ruin (as if overturned) -- heap. see HEBREW (H5753) avah
Or (feminine) uaya((Neh. 11:31) {ah-yaw'}; or eayath (Isaiah 10:28) {ah-yawth'}; for (H5856) iy; Ai, Aja or Ajath, a place in Palestine -- Ai, Aija, Aijath, Hai. see HEBREW (H5856) iy
Perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be bald; bare; Ebal, a mountain of Palestine -- Ebal.
From (H5856) iy; ruin; Ijon, a place in Palestine -- Ijon. see HEBREW (H5856) iy
A primitive root; to swoop down upon (literally or figuratively) -- fly, rail.
From (H5860) iyt; a hawk or other bird of prey -- bird, fowl, ravenous (bird). see HEBREW (H5860) iyt
From (H5861) ayit; hawk-ground; Etam, a place in Palestine -- Etam. see HEBREW (H5861) ayit

column7: a place on the E. border of Moab, also a city in S. Judah
column9: From the plural of (H5856) iy and the plural of the active participle of (H5674) abar with the article interposed; ruins of the passers; Ije-ha-Abarim, a place near Palestine -- Ije-abarim. see HEBREW (H5856) iy see HEBREW (H5674) abar

column7: a place on the E. border of Moab
column9: Plural of (H5856) iy; ruins; Ijim, a place in the Desert. -- Iim. see HEBREW (H5856) iy
For (H5769) owlam -- ever. see HEBREW (H5769) owlam
From (H5927) alah; elevated; Ilai, an Israelite -- Ilai. see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column4: proper name, of a people et. terr.; proper name, masculine
column7: a son of Shem, also his desc. and their country
column9: Or mowlam (Ezra 10:2; Jeremiah 49:36) {o-lawm'}; probably from (H5956) alam; hidden, i.e. Distant; Elam, a son of Shem and his descendants, with their country; also of six Israelites -- Elam. see HEBREW (H5956) alam
Of doubtful origin and authenticity; probably meaning strength -- mighty.

column8: affliction, outward appearance, before, think best, color, conceit, be content
column9: Probably a primitive word; an eye (literally or figuratively); by analogy, a fountain (as the eye of the landscape) -- affliction, outward appearance, + before, + think best, colour, conceit, + be content, countenance, + displease, eye((-brow), (-d), -sight), face, + favour, fountain, furrow (from the margin), X him, + humble, knowledge, look, (+ well), X me, open(-ly), + (not) please, presence, + regard, resemblance, sight, X thee, X them, + think, X us, well, X you(-rselves).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5869) ayin; an eye -- eye. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin
The same as (H5869) ayin; fountain; Ajin, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine -- Ain. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin

column7: spring of a kid, a place on west shore of the Dead Sea
column9: From (H5869) ayin and (H1423) gdiy; fountain of a kid; En-Gedi, a place in Palestine -- En-gedi. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H1423) gdiy

column7: spring of a garden, two places in Isr
column9: From (H5869) ayin and the plural of (H1588) gan; fountain of gardens; En-Gannim, a place in Palestine -- En-gannim. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H1588) gan

column5: En-dor or En Dor or En-dor
column7: spring of dwelling, a town in Manasseh
column9: Or meyn Dowr {ane dore}; or Eyn-Dor {ane-dore'}; from (H5869) ayin and (H1755) dowr; fountain of dwelling; En-Dor, a place in Palestine -- En-dor. see HEBREW (H1755) dowr

column7: spring of the one calling, location of a miraculous spring
column9: From (H5869) ayin and the active participle of (H7121) qara'; fountain of One calling; En-hak-Kore, a place near Palestine -- En-hakhore. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H7121) qara'

column7: spring of sharpness, a place in Issachar
column9: From (H5869) ayin and the feminine of a derivative from (H2300) chadad; fountain of sharpness; En-Chaddah, a place in Palestine -- En-haddah. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H2300) chadad

column7: a spring of Hazor, a city in Naphtali
column9: From (H5869) ayin and the same as (H2674) Chatsowr; fountain of a village; En-Chatsor, a place in Palestine -- En-hazor. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H2674) Chatsowr

column7: En-Charod, a place in Palestine -- well of Harod
column8: En-Charod, a place in Palestine -- well of Harod
column9: From (H5869) ayin and a derivative of (H2729) charad; fountain of trembling; En-Charod, a place in Palestine -- well of Harod. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H2729) charad

column7: two springs, a place in Isr
column9: Or meynam {ay-nawm'}; dual of (H5869) ayin; double fountain; Enajim or Enam, a place in Palestine -- Enaim, openly (Genesis 38:21). see HEBREW (H5869) ayin

column7: spring of judgment, another name for a place called Kadesh
column9: From (H5869) ayin and (H4941) mishpat; fountain of judgment; En-Mishpat, a place near Palestine -- En-mishpat. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H4941) mishpat

column7: having fountains, a man of Naphtali
column9: From (H5869) ayin; having eyes; Enan, an Israelite -- Enan. Compare (H2704) Chatsar 'Eynan. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H2704) Chatsar 'Eynan

column7: spring of two calves, a place on the Dead Sea
column9: (H5869) ayin and the dual of (H5695) egel; fountain of two calves; En-Eglajim, a place in Palestine -- En-eglaim. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H5695) egel
From (H5869) ayin and the active participle of (H7270) ragal; fountain of a traveller; En-Rogel, a place near Jerusalem: see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H7270) ragal

column7: spring of a pomegranate, a place in Judah
column9: From (H5869) ayin and (H7416) rimmown; fountain of a pomegranate; En-Rimmon, a place in Palestine -- En-rimmon. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H7416) rimmown

column7: spring of (the) sun, a place on the border between Judah and Benjamin
column9: From (H5869) ayin and (H8121) shemesh; fountain of the sun; En-Shemesh, a place in Palestine -- En-shemesh. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh

column7: spring of dragons, a place near Jer
column9: From (H5869) ayin and the plural of (H8565) tan; fountain of jackals; En-Tannim, a pool near Jerusalem -- dragon well. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H8565) tan

column7: place of an apple tree, a city in Ephraim
column9: From (H5869) ayin and (H8598) tappuwach; fountain of an apple-tree; En-Tappuach, a place in Palestine -- En-tappuah. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin see HEBREW (H8598) tappuwach
A primitive root; to languish -- be wearied.
From (H5888) ayeph; languid -- faint, thirsty, weary. see HEBREW (H5888) ayeph
Feminine from (H5774) uwph; obscurity (as if from covering) -- darkness. see HEBREW (H5774) uwph

column4: proper name; of a people; masculine; feminine
column9: The same as (H5890) eyphah; Ephah, the name of a son of Midian, and of the region settled by him; also of an Israelite and of an Israelitess -- Ephah. see HEBREW (H5890) eyphah

Or (in the plural) par {awr}; or ayar (Judges 10:4) {aw-yar'}; from (H5782) uwr a city (a place guarded by waking or a watch) in the widest sense (even of a mere encampment or post) -- Ai (from margin), city, court (from margin), town. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
The same as (H5892) iyr; Ir, an Israelite -- Ir. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H5782) uwr; a watcher, i.e. An angel (as guardian) -- watcher. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
From (H5782) uwr in the sense of raising (i.e. Bearing a burden); properly, a young ass (as just broken to a load); hence an ass-colt -- (ass) colt, foal, young ass. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
From (H5782) uwr; wakefulness; Ira, the name of three Israelites -- Ira. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
From the same as (H6166) Arad; fugitive; Irad, an antediluvian -- Irad. see HEBREW (H6166) Arad

column7: city of salt, a place in the Judean desert
column8: Ir-ham-Melach, a place near Palestine -- the city of salt
column9: From (H5892) iyr and (H4417) melach with the article of substance interp.; city of (the) salt; Ir-ham-Melach, a place near Palestine -- the city of salt. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr see HEBREW (H4417) melach

column7: Ir-hat-Temarim, a place in Palestine -- the city of palm trees
column8: Ir-hat-Temarim, a place in Palestine -- the city of palm trees
column9: From (H5892) iyr and the plural of (H8558) tamar with the article interpolated; city of the palmtrees; Ir-hat-Temarim, a place in Palestine -- the city of palmtrees. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr see HEBREW (H8558) tamar
From (H5892) iyr; a citizen; Iru, an Israelite -- Iru. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr
From (H5892) iyr; urbane; Iri, an Israelite -- Iri. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr
From (H5892) iyr; city-wise; Iram, an Idumaean -- Iram. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr

column4: Adjective; noun masculine; Adjective; noun abstract
column9: Or merom {ay-rome'}; from (H6191) aram; nudity -- naked(- ness). see HEBREW (H6191) aram

column7: city of a serpent, a city in Judah
column9: From (H5892) iyr and (H5175) nachash; city of a serpent; Ir-Nachash, a place in Palestine -- Ir-nahash. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr see HEBREW (H5175) nachash

column7: city of the sun, a city in Dan
column9: From (H5892) iyr and (H8121) shemesh; city of the sun; Ir-Shemesh, a place in Palestine -- Ir-shemesh. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh
Or Ash {awsh}; from (H5789) uwsh; the constellation of the Great Bear (perhaps from its migration through the heavens) -- Arcturus. see HEBREW (H5789) uwsh

column7: mouse, an Israelite, also an Edomite
column9: Probably for (H5909) akbar; Akbor, the name of an Idumaean and of two Israelites -- Achbor. see HEBREW (H5909) akbar
Probably from an unused root in the literal sense of entangling; a spider (as weaving a network) -- spider.
Probably from the same as (H5908) akkabiysh in the secondary sense of attacking; a mouse (as nibbling) -- mouse. see HEBREW (H5908) akkabiysh
Apparently from an unused root meaning to hem in; Akko (from its situation on a bay) -- Accho.

column7: disturbance, a valley on the border of Judah
column9: From (H5916) akar; troubled; Akor, the name of a place in Palestine -- Achor. see HEBREW (H5916) akar
From an unused root meaning to trouble; troublesome; Akan, an Israelite -- Achan. Compare (H5917) Akar. see HEBREW (H5917) Akar

column8: make a tinkling ornament,  put on anklets
column9: A primitive root; properly, to tie, specifically, with fetters; but used only as denominative from (H5914) ekec; to put on anklets -- make a tinkling ornament. see HEBREW (H5914) ekec
From (H5913) akac; a fetter; hence, an anklet -- stocks, tinkling ornament. see HEBREW (H5913) akac
Feminine of (H5914) ekec; anklet; Aksah, an Israelitess -- Achsah. see HEBREW (H5914) ekec
A primitive root; properly, to roil water; figuratively, to disturb or affict -- trouble, stir.
From (H5916) akar; troublesome; Akar, an Israelite -- Achar. Compare (H5912) Akan. see HEBREW (H5916) akar see HEBREW (H5912) Akan
From (H5916) akar; muddler; Okran, an Israelite -- Ocran. see HEBREW (H5916) akar
Probably from an unused root meaning to coil; an asp (from lurking coiled up) -- adder.
From (H5927) alah; properly, the top; specifically, the highest (i.e. God); also (adverb) aloft, to Jehovah -- above, high, most High. see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column8: above, according to, after, as against, among, and, as, at,
column9: Properly, the same as (H5920) al used as a preposition (in the singular or plural often with prefix, or as conjunction with a particle following); above, over, upon, or against (yet always in this last relation with a downward aspect) in a great variety of applications (as follow) -- above, according to(-ly), after, (as) against, among, and, X as, at, because of, beside (the rest of), between, beyond the time, X both and, by (reason of), X had the charge of, concerning for, in (that), (forth, out) of, (from) (off), (up-)on, over, than, through(-out), to, touching, X with. see HEBREW (H5920) al
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5921) al -- about, against, concerning, for, (there-)fore, from, in, X more, of, (there-, up-)on, (in-)to, + why with. see HEBREW (H5921) al
Or mowl {ole}; from (H5953) alal; a yoke (as imposed on the neck), literally or figuratively -- yoke. see HEBREW (H5953) alal
(Aramaic) from (H5922) al; above -- over. see HEBREW (H5922) al
Feminine of (H5923) ol; burden; Ulla, an Israelite -- Ulla. see HEBREW (H5923) ol
From an unused root meaning to stutter; stuttering -- stammerer.

column8: arise up, cause to ascend up, at once, break the day up, bring up, cause to burn
column9: A primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative (as follow) -- arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up, + shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, X mention, mount up, offer, make to pay, + perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5930) olah; a holocaust -- burnt offering. see HEBREW (H5930) olah
From (H5927) alah; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage -- branch, leaf. see HEBREW (H5927) alah

Or mowlah {o-law'}; feminine active participle of (H5927) alah; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke) -- ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also (H5766) evel. see HEBREW (H5927) alah see HEBREW (H5766) evel
(Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to (H5927) alah; a pretext (as arising artificially) -- occasion. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
For (H5766) evel; moral perverseness -- iniquity. see HEBREW (H5766) evel
Or Alyah {al-yaw'}; the same as (H5932) alvah; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean -- Aliah, Alvah. see HEBREW (H5932) alvah
Passive participle of (H5956) alam in the denominative sense of (H5958) elem; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor -- youth. see HEBREW (H5956) alam see HEBREW (H5958) elem
Or salyan {al-yawn'}; from (H5927) alah; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean -- Alian, Alvan. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
Feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech -- horse-leech.
A primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. Exult -- be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
From (H5937) alaz; exultant -- that rejoiceth. see HEBREW (H5937) alaz
Feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk -- dark, twilight.
From (H5927) alah; a pestle (as lifted) -- pestle. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
From (H5927) alah; lofty; Eli, an Israelite high-priest -- Eli. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
From (H5927) alah; high; i.e. Comparative -- upper. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5942) illiy; supreme (i.e. God) -- (most) high. see HEBREW (H5942) illiy

column8: ascent, upper chamber, going up, loft, parlor
column9: Feminine from (H5927) alah; something lofty, i.e. A stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky -- ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
From (H5927) alah; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) Lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme -- (Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most). see HEBREW (H5927) alah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5945) 'elyown; the Supreme -- Most high. see HEBREW (H5945) 'elyown
From (H5937) alaz; exultant -- joyous, (that) rejoice(-ing) see HEBREW (H5937) alaz
From (H5953) alal in the sense of completing; probably a crucible (as working over the metal) -- furnace. see HEBREW (H5953) alal

column8: action, deed, doing, invention, occasion, work
column9: Or malilah {al-ee-law'}; from (H5953) alal in the sense of effecting; an exploit (of God), or a performance (of man, often in a bad sense); by implication, an opportunity -- act(-ion), deed, doing, invention, occasion, work. see HEBREW (H5953) alal
For (H5949) aliylah; (miraculous) execution -- work. see HEBREW (H5949) aliylah
From (H5970) alats; exultation -- rejoicing. see HEBREW (H5970) alats
From (H5927) alah; a second-story room -- chamber. Compare (H5944) aliyah. see HEBREW (H5927) alah see HEBREW (H5944) aliyah

column8: abuse, affect, child, defile, do, glean, mock, practice,
column9: A primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. Maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal) -- abuse, affect, X child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).

column8: bring in, come in, go in
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H5953) alal (in the sense of thrusting oneself in), to enter; causatively, to introduce -- bring in, come in, go in. see HEBREW (H5953) alal
Feminine active participle of (H5953) alal; only in plural gleanings; by extens. Gleaning-time -- (gleaning) (of the) grapes, grapegleanings. see HEBREW (H5953) alal

column8: blind, dissembler, hide self, secret thing
column9: A primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. Conceal (literally or figuratively) -- X any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5769) owlam; remote time, i.e. The future or past indefinitely; often adverb, forever -- for ((n-))ever (lasting), old. see HEBREW (H5769) owlam
From (H5956) alam; properly, something kept out of sight (compare (H5959) almah), i.e. A lad -- young man, stripling. see HEBREW (H5956) alam see HEBREW (H5959) almah
Feminine of (H5958) elem; a lass (as veiled or private) -- damsel, maid, virgin. see HEBREW (H5958) elem
From (H5956) alam; hidden; Almon, a place in Palestine See also (H5963) Almon Diblathaymah. see HEBREW (H5956) alam see HEBREW (H5963) Almon Diblathaymah
Plural of (H5959) almah; properly, girls, i.e. The soprano or female voice, perhaps falsetto -- Alamoth. see HEBREW (H5959) almah
(Aramaic) patrial from a name corresponding to (H5867) Eylam contracted; an Elamite or inhabitant of Elam -- Elamite.

From the same as (H5960) Almown and the dual of (H1690) dbelah (compare (H1015) Beyth Diblathayim) with enclitic of direction; Almon towards Diblathajim; Almon-Diblathajemah, a place in Moab: see HEBREW (H5960) Almown see HEBREW (H1690) dbelah see HEBREW (H1015) Beyth Diblathayim

column4: proper name, masculine person; proper name, of a location
column7: a Benjamite name, also a Levitical city in Benjamin
column9: From (H5956) alam; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites -- Alameth, Alemeth. see HEBREW (H5956) alam
A primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. Exult, wave joyously -- X peacock, rejoice, solace self.
A prim root; to sip up -- suck up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6763) tsela'; a rib -- rib. see HEBREW (H6763) tsela'
A primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid -- faint, overlaid, wrap self.
From (H5968) alaph; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning -- fainted. see HEBREW (H5968) alaph
A primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. Exult -- be joyful, rejoice, triumph.

From (H6004) amam; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock -- folk, men, nation, people. see HEBREW (H6004) amam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5971) am -- people. see HEBREW (H5971) am

column8: accompanying, against, and, as long as, before, beside, by reason of, for all,
column9: From (H6004) amam; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. In conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English) -- accompanying, against, and, as (X long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of, (un-)to, with(-al). see HEBREW (H6004) amam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5973) im -- by, from, like, to(-ward), with. see HEBREW (H5973) im

column8: abide behind, appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed,
column9: A primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive) -- abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair, + serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-)stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.
For (H4571) ma'ad; to shake -- be at a stand. see HEBREW (H4571) ma'ad
From (H5975) amad; a spot (as being fixed) -- place, (+ where) stood, upright. see HEBREW (H5975) amad

column7: against, by, from, me, mine, of, that I take, unto,
column8: against, by, from, me, mine, of, that I take, unto,
column9: Prol. For (H5973) im; along with -- against, by, from, + me, + mine, of, + that I take, unto, upon, with(-in.) see HEBREW (H5973) im
From (H5975) amad; a station, i.e. Domicile -- standing. see HEBREW (H5975) amad

column7: close by, side by side with
column8: over against, at, beside, hard by, in points
column9: From (H6004) amam; conjunction, i.e. Society; mostly adverb or preposition (with prepositional prefix), near, beside, along with -- (over) against, at, beside, hard by, in points. see HEBREW (H6004) amam
The same as (H5980) ummah; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine -- Ummah. see HEBREW (H5980) ummah
Or ammud {am-mood'}; from (H5975) amad; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. Platform -- X apiece, pillar. see HEBREW (H5975) amad

column7: a people living East of the Jordan
column9: From (H5971) am; tribal, i.e. Inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country -- Ammon, Ammonites. see HEBREW (H5971) am
Patronymically from (H5983) Ammown; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish -- Ammonite(-s). see HEBREW (H5983) Ammown
Feminine of (H5984) Ammowniy; an Ammonitess -- Ammonite(-ss). see HEBREW (H5984) Ammowniy
From (H6006) amac; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet -- Amos. see HEBREW (H6006) amac
From (H6009) amaq; deep; Amok, an Israelite -- Amok. see HEBREW (H6009) amaq

column7: my kinsman is God, four Israelites
column9: From (H5971) am and (H410) 'el; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites -- Ammiel. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: my kinsman is majesty, four Israelites, also a Geshurite
column9: From (H5971) am and (H1935) howd; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites -- Ammihud. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H1935) howd

column7: my kinsman has bestowed, an Israelite
column9: From (H5971) am and (H2064) zabad; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite -- Ammizabad. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H2064) zabad
From (H5971) am and (H2353) chuwr; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince -- Ammihud (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr

column7: my kinsman is noble, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H5971) am and (H5068) nadab; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites -- Amminadab. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H5068) nadab
From (H5971) am and (H5081) nadiyb; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite -- Amminadib. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H5081) nadiyb
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6012) ameq; profound, i.e. Unsearchable, deep. see HEBREW (H6012) ameq

column7: a swath, row of fallen grain
column9: From (H6014) amar; a bunch of grain -- handful, sheaf. see HEBREW (H6014) amar

column7: my kinsman is Shaddai, a Danite
column9: From (H5971) am and (H7706) Shadday; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite -- Ammishaddai. see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H7706) Shadday
From a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man -- another, fellow, neighbour.
A primitive root; to toil, i.e. Work severely and with irksomeness -- (take) labour (in).

column8: grievance, iniquity, labor, mischief, misery, painful, perverseness, sorrow,
column9: From (H5998) amal; toil, i.e. Wearing effort; hence, worry, wheth. Of body or mind -- grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness. see HEBREW (H5998) amal
